title: mostaccioli al forno
directions: In large bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese, 2/3 cup Mozzarella cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: chicken curry
directions: Clean, wash and dry the chicken.
Grind or chop onions, garlic and ginger.
Heat the oil and fry the onion, garlic and ginger until golden brown.
Add chicken pieces, salt and all the spices and fry for 10 to 12 minutes, until the oil leaves the side of the pan.
Add about 2 cups water and simmer on slow fire until chicken is cooked and gravy is thick.
Sprinkle some coriander leaves and serve with white rice.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts, fruit and chocolate bits; mix lightly.
Beat eggs and sugar together and stir into first mixture.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with brown paper; butter paper.
Pour in mix.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bread is best if stored and well-wrapped for a day or two before slicing.
Best if sliced thin.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter in a shallow baking pan.
Add the pecans and stir to coat with butter.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until pecans are toasted, stirring frequently. Sift flour with baking powder and salt and set aside.
Cream the remaining 1 cup of butter with the sugar, adding the sugar gradually and creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in the vanilla extract and 1 1/3 cups of toasted pecans.
Save the remaining 2/3 cup toasted pecans to use in the frosting.
Pour the batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Cool on wire racks.

title: bread n butter pickles
directions: May use less onions, if desired.
Slice cucumbers and onions. Let stand 1 hour in water after sprinkling with salt.
Let spices and vinegar with the sugar come to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack into pint jars and water bath for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter rice chex
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter chips.
Add peanut butter (small jar Jif).
Pour over rice cereal.
Mix well.

title: holly cookies
directions: Heat butter and marshmallows until completely melted.
Add color.
Add cornflakes.
Stir.
Quickly drop by spoonful on wax paper to resemble holly.
Decorate immediately with red hots. Very easy and very pretty for Christmas.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk and flour, mixing well.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in preheated 325° oven.

title: rosy apple punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot apple juice in medium bowl.
Add cold apple juice and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes about 8 (5 ounce) servings.

title: chicken with artichokes
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain.
Add onions, mushrooms, artichoke hearts and garlic to the drippings in the pan.
Saute for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Cook over medium heat.
Bring to boil; stir occasionally.
When it's at a full boil, add jello and stir.
Boil 15 minutes.
Put in sterile jars; seal.
Store in refrigerator.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Boil ribs, 15 minutes per pound. Mix all ingredients for sauce. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Drain ribs. Place, meaty side up, in roaster. Cover with sauce. Roast 1 1/2 hours at 350°, basting with sauce occasionally.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Add all together; use jello dry.
Drain pineapple, cut oranges up.
Save some to garnish top.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine marshmallows, rice, fruit and nuts.
Whip cream; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into rice mixture.
Chill. Makes 8 servings.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Cut frozen fish into chunks; set aside.

Combine oil, green pepper, celery, onion and garlic in skillet; cook until tender. Add fish, tomatoes, clam juice, basil, salt and pepper in large pot; cook until fish is tender (done when fish is flaky).
Add clams and liquid; stir.
Add remaining ingredients (green pepper, celery and onion).
Cook for 1 hour.
Serve with fresh baked bread.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: aunt martha's arroz con pollo
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Set aside.
Grind comino and peppercorns together.
Add garlic.
Grind together and add a little water.
Put aside.

title: potato-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and then drain well.
After cubing potatoes, cook until done.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in 3/4 cup butter. (A pastry blender or 2 knives can be used.)
Press this mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes until light brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until tender.
Reduce heat to simmer and add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and chili peppers.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, coffee, cream and corn syrup.
Stir constantly while bringing to a boil.
Boil steadily without further stirring, until soft ball is formed.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Butter a long tin and put in nuts and marshmallows.
Pour candy over these, then slice.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix
sugar,
peanut
butter
and
butter, kneading with hands if necessary.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on jelly roll
pan. Cover
and
refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours. In
heavy saucepan
(1 quart size), melt chocolate pieces and shortening over low heat.
When melted, add paraffin.	Remove half
of peanut butter balls from refrigerator.
Using toothpick, carefully
dip
balls one at a time into chocolate mixture, making
sure
to
leave a small amount of peanut butter showing on	top
to
resemble
an eye.
Place coated balls on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Repeat process for rest of
the peanut butter balls.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Mix flour and margarine in medium saucepan over medium to low heat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Place potatoes in serving dish and pour sauce over them.
Top with cheese, if desired. Serve immediately or place in oven to keep warm.

title: janie's famous no-cook yogurt ice cream
directions: Combine clear jell and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in the order given, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Pour into 8-quart ice cream freezer and freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: baked red onion
directions: Peel and cut onions in half crosswise.
Place side by side, cut-side up, in a shallow 8-inch (20 cm) baking pan.
In a small bowl, blend together the vinegar, water, sugar replacement, salt, sage and mustard.
Pour over onion halves.
Bake at 350° (175° C) for 50 to 60 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle cookie crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan. Set aside. Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add cream cheese, sugar, cottage cheese, cocoa, flour, Amaretto, vanilla and salt, processing until smooth.
Add egg and process just until blended. Fold in morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan. Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cheesecake is set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Remove sides of pan and transfer cheesecake onto a serving platter. Decorate with chips, chocolate curls and/or almonds.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add in order given.
Bake in moderate oven until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french silk pie
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Melt chocolate separately in a double boiler.
Set over hot water.
Mix chocolate, butter and sugar in a mixer on high speed for 8 minutes, then add eggs, one at a time.
Fill pie shell with chocolate mixture and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish pie with almonds or chocolate.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Roll the dough in your hands.
Put in pan.
Cook in oven 20 minutes.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in the 2 cups of water until water evaporates. Add to applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend all ingredients together; mix until moistened.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: yogurt baked chicken
directions: Combine yogurt, lemon juice, soy sauce, coriander, curry powder and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Turn chicken breasts in sauce to coat all sides.
Cover and marinate several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all except Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix.
Refrigerate. Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: easy taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain off fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: braunschweiger burger
directions: Fry bacon (2 strips each burger) until crisp.
Drain, reserving fat.
Brown 1/2-inch braunschweiger slices in a little bacon fat over medium heat about 2 minutes per side.
Careful, don't overcook.

title: strawberries and cream salad
directions: Dissolve 1 (3 ounce) package strawberry gelatin and 1 (3 ounce) package raspberry gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool. Mash 3 medium ripe bananas or puree in blender.
Blend into gelatin.
Stir in 1 cup crushed pineapple and 2 cups sliced fresh strawberries, sweetened with 1/2 cup sugar.
(Two 10 ounce packages frozen sweetened strawberries may be substituted.)
Chill until mixture mounds from a spoon.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl; cook bacon in skillet to desired crispness.
Remove bacon; drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Add onion and celery; cook and stir until celery is tender.
Blend in flour.
Stir in dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade pumpkin pie spice
directions: Mix together and use in your pumpkin pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put some of beef or ham in mixture, but retain some to roll the ball in.
Mix remaining ingredients and form into ball.
Roll in retained beef or ham.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Combine crackers and butter and press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix pudding and milk at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add ice cream.
Freeze and top with Cool Whip and grated Heath bar.

title: country style hot dog relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together on coarse blade of grinder (I use food processor).
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to a full boil and boil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in clean, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 9 pints.

title: homemade irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator for up to 1 month.
Stir before serving.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt in a large mixing bowl. Put butter, water and cocoa in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over the sugar-flour mixture. Stir well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in greased 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Combine ingredients and cook until it will form a soft ball in cold water.
Take from heat and add 1/4 stick butter.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a greased platter.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients to the consistency of custard. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat well; serve over noodles.
This freezes well, just thaw, heat thoroughly and pour over fresh cooked noodles.

title: chili con queso
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, place soup, garlic salt and a small amount of milk to thin.
Break up soup and watch closely. Add drained chopped green chili to the mixture and reduce heat to simmer until heated through.
Serve as a dip or cover Mexican food dishes.
If cool from the refrigerator, fold into a meat loaf before baking, covering top of the meat loaf with medium salsa instead of ketchup.
Use corn chips (white or regular).

title: gelatin salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; add pineapple with juice.
Add pecans and apple.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine with peanut butter. Add sugars, vanilla, soda and eggs.
Blend well.
Mix in oatmeal, chocolate chips and M&M's slowly, blending well.
Use 1/4 measuring cup to dip dough.
Flatten cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.
After cooling 1 to 2 minutes, carefully remove to paper towel.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Soak raisins until plump; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Add all other ingredients, sauteed in oleo.
Blend well.
This is enough for two casseroles.
Freezes well.
Bake in 200° oven.
If desired, top with grated cheese and melt the cheese just before serving.

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Combine sugar and water; stir until dissolved.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; boil gently for 10 minutes.
Remove from
heat; cool lightly and add vanilla and maple flavoring.
Stir only until mixed.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: german beef tips
directions: Place stewing beef in a crock-pot.
Add potato salad on top of meat.
Do not mix.
Cook in crock-pot all day on low.
Serve with a vegetable and/or a salad.

title: "the dish"(tagliarini)
directions: Saute meat in small amount of vegetable oil.
Add onions and peppers and cook until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Cook mixture for 45 minutes. Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and add along with cheese to meat sauce mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses set out to soften for 2 hours, then mix both cheese products together.
Add all other ingredients and blend with a mixer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, cocoa and flour. Remove from heat, beat in eggs, one at a time; then vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (center may still be soft).
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes (center will become firm).
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chick-a-pamushroom(chicken dish)
directions: Debone chicken.
Add additional ingredients to chicken broth in following order:
Rice and pasta according to package directions, mushroom soup mix and mushroom pieces according to directions on soup mix and put chicken back into the mixture.

title: danish sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water (115°).
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt; mix well.
Cut in cold oleo until mixture is the consistency of corn meal.
By hand, stir in yeast, egg yolks and milk to form soft dough.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough (next day) into halves.
Roll on floured board to a 9 x 14-inch rectangle.
Spread with filling made by combining butter, sugar and coconut.
Roll in jelly roll fashion, then cut evenly.
Place on a greased baking sheet to rise.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Repeat with remainder of dough, but use 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup raisins and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon.
Mix together for filling.

title: meat loaf
directions: Spread catsup over top 30 minutes before removing from oven. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jim's favorite chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Turn and baste chicken every 15 minutes.

title: spicy queso
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Drain and set aside.
In a large bowl, chop Velveeta into small blocks.
Add Ro-Tel and microwave for 5 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Add meat and mix well.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Chop fresh spinach and steam in 2-inch water until tender; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in melted margarine.
Stir in flour. Add spinach (do not drain).
Simmer 15 minutes with onion and celery.
Add milk, cheese and seasonings; allow to heat.
Slowly stir in cream.
If thicker soup is desired, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch, dissolved in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Serves approximately 8.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion, green and red pepper and celery in oil in a small saucepan, stirring, about 4 minutes until vegetables are softened. Stir in broth, water, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Lower heat and simmer, covered,
for 25 minutes, or until rice is fork-tender.

title: carolina mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes; drain well. Add all other ingredients except milk.
Mix well, adding milk a little at a time.
(Don't let potatoes get too mushy.)
Put in casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add last 3 ingredients and stir well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with vanilla or cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend together flour, nuts and margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together; spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding, vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread extra Cool Whip over top.
Chill overnight.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 1/4 cup of pudding mixture to spread on crackers.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; put them in the freezer.
Makes 24 long or 48 short.

title: roast turkey and dressing
directions: Stuff turkey cavities; truss.
Place breast side up in roasting pan.
Lightly grease with butter or margarine.
Roast in a preheated 325° oven for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Let stand with an aluminum foil tent over for about 20 minutes.
Make gravy with the pan drippings.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, mixing well and pour over steak. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain meat and broil steak to desired doneness.
Slice across grain in thin slices. Store remaining marinade for future use.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk, well.
Put mixture in freezer and fill up to line
with
sweet
milk.
Add fruit, if desired.

title: crab stuffed cajun fish
directions: In a skillet melt the butter and add the onions, celery and garlic.
Simmer until the vegetables are tender.
Meanwhile, prepare the fish fillets.
Thick fillets are best but you can also use thinner fillets.
With a sharp knife, make a slit lengthwise. Make a pouch in the fillet.
Be careful not to cut through the fillet.
If you have small fillets and pieces overlap them the best you can and use toothpicks to hold them together.
When the vegetables are tender add the bread crumbs and the crabmeat.
Mix well.
You may have to add more bread crumbs or butter to get a good, workable stuffing mixture.
Place a heaping spoonful (or as much as you can get in the fillet) of the stuffing mixture in each fillet and mold with your hands.
Then place on a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Cajun seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Put pineapple in dish.
Cut marshmallows in four pieces and put over pineapple.
Pour cream over mixture.
Leave it set for 10 to 12 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: curry lamb
directions: Cut lamb into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is lightly brown.
Remove and discard garlic.
Add curry powder, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add lamb, celery, apple and enough boiling water to cover.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until lamb is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream cheese and sour cream and chill.
After chilled, add the remaining ingredients.
Return to fridge and chill well before serving.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice potatoes and onions.
Cook together with 2 teaspoons salt until done.
Drain and reserve water.
Combine melted butter and flour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Bring chicken, eggs, cubes and garlic to a boil in a big cooking pot. Cook until chicken is done. Remove chicken and eggs from broth (do not discard broth). Let cool. Remove chicken off the bone (discard fat). Slice eggs and set aside. Take Annie's Dumplings and slice each one lengthwise. Add to boiling broth. Cook 5 to 6 minutes until done. Add milk, chicken and eggs. Put a tablespoon of cornstarch in cup and mix with water to paste. Add to chicken and dumplings until the mixture becomes slightly thickened.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine butter and water in a 4 qt. dutch oven; Cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Add sugar and salt, mixing well. Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Boil gently until mixture begins to lighten in color.
Add 1 c. pecans.
Continue cooking stirring constantly until candy thermometer reaches 298 degrees. Pour mixture into foil lined jelly roll pan, spreading to the edges.
Cool slightly, mark into squares using the sharp edge of a knife.
Cool thoroughly.
Melt chocolate.
Spread over toffee, sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Let cool and break into squares.

title: dandelion quiche
directions: Saute onion and ham in butter.
Lightly mix with all other ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hidden valley holiday torta
directions: Cream the cream cheese and dressing mix together.
In a separate bowl, stir together artichoke hearts, peppers and parsley (or dill).
Line a 3-cup bowl with plastic wrap, alternate layers of cheese and vegetable mixture (begin and end with a cheese layer).
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Invert on plate; remove plastic wrap.
Serve with crackers.

title: deer meat chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in heavy skillet; drain off all excess fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir and cook over low heat for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
The honey and garlic take away the wild taste of the deer meat.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 16 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and put in separate bowl.
Mash yolks with fork.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg whites.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Sprinkle bacon bits or paprika on top of eggs for garnish.

title: john chapham's whole baked salmon
directions: Place the whole salmon on a generous piece of foil.
Slice the oranges and lemons, peel and all.
Peel and slice the onion. Place 3 or 4 blobs of butter on the fish and a row or oranges, lemons and onion.
Distribute the rest of the butter over and around the fish, ditto for the oranges, lemons and onion.
Keep a few slices of citrus for garnish.
Season lightly with seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Wrap the fish securely in the foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in the center of your oven; garnish with parsley.

title: aunt pauline's "brown sugar cookies"
directions: Mix well; chill dough 2 hours.
Dough will need flour kneaded into it to ready it for rolling out into cookies.
Great for Christmas cookies or anytime.
Roll thick cookies for soft ones or thin cookies for crispier ones.
To make sandwich cookies with preserves in between, bake filled cookies in oven at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Bake crust until browned.
Cool well.
Combine mayonnaise and flour and blend with wire whisk.
Mix egg and milk and add slowly, blending with whisk.
Stir in well drained crab, cheese and onion. Spoon into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is firm.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil, egg and sugar.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° until light brown.
Drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Makes about 8 to 9 dozen.

title: orange-spiced carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Combine next 6 ingredients. Add carrots stirring until slightly thickened.
Add margarine and stir.
Yield 4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut up in small pieces and place in baking dish (9 x 13-inches).
Spread 1 can cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix together stuffing, onion, poultry seasoning, sage and melted margarine.
Add enough broth to make a smooth mixture and pour over chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange on pizza pan, overlapping edges and mashing together to form crust layer. Bake at 350 to 375° for 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Allow to cool.
Blend together cream cheese, sugar, extract and whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Prepare 5 or 6 fruits. Arrange in circles over cream cheese layer.
Cover as much of the layer as possible, to have generous fruit portions on each serving.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Break sausage into pieces in a cold skillet.
Fry slowly for 12 to 15 minutes, until evenly brown, pouring off fat as it accumulates.
Add rice to fat in skillet.
Cook and stir over low heat until rice is lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, onion, salt, chili powder, hot water and sausage.
Pour into a baking dish and cook, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: german rouladen(braised stuffed beef rolls)
directions: Arrange bacon slices on meat; top with Swiss cheese.
Combine the ground chuck, egg, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, paprika, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and oil; mix well.
Divide this mixture equally for each piece of meat.
Spread on meat, roll up and tie with thin kite string.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine cinnamon and sugar in small bowl.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in 10-inch well-greased Bundt pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Invert on serving plate.
Pull apart and enjoy.

title: orange drop doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in sugar and shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture alternately with orange juice and rind.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into hot fat (375°). Dip two spoons in grease to drop dough into grease.

title: chocolate sheet cake(do not use electric mixer)
directions: Sift flour; add sugar and salt.
In another pan, bring water to a boil.
Add cocoa, oil and margarine; pour liquid into dry ingredients (do not use electric mixer).
While mixing, add 2 eggs, 1/2 cup buttermilk, vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Batter is very thin.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until the edges break away from the sides of the pan.

title: raisin brownies
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the graham cracker crumbs; set aside.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl and set aside. Separate biscuits into individual biscuits.
Gently separate each biscuit in half. Place a cream cheese square between the two halves, pinch sides together.
Dip in butter, and dredge in reserved sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in a lightly greased bundt pan spacing evenly.
Drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert onto serving plate. Combine sugar and orange juice.
Drizzle over warm bread.
Serve immediately.

title: flaky pineapple squares
directions: Cut margarine or butter into flour with pastry blender.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cook pineapple, sugar and cornstarch over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Cool.

title: miniature ham puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed, golden brown and dry, about 25 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Blend remaining ingredients; refrigerate.
Just before serving, cut off tops of puffs with sharp knife; remove any filaments of soft dough.
Fill each puff with rounded teaspoons of ham mixture.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Store pie shell in refrigerator.
Use double boiler and scald milk.
While heating the milk, beat with mixer, the eggs until mixed.
Add other ingredients except vanilla.
Add to milk, stir and add vanilla.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix and spread on cooled dough.
Roll up and wrap or cover. Keep refrigerated.

title: good chili
directions: Heat oil.
Crumble and brown beef until no longer pink.
Puree onion soup in blender and pour over beef.
Simmer about 5 minutes. Add spices, undrained beans, tomato paste and sauce.
Stir until combined.
Simmer over low heat at least 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Enjoy!

title: baked fruit
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Pour over fruit, mix well.
Bake in 2 1/2-quart dish at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: grandma nettie's hamburger 'n mushroom gravy(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into 10 oval patties.
Using a frying pan, brown both sides in oil, then move to a 13 x9-inch pan.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white (at room temperature) and water at high speed until foamy.
Add pecans, stirring to coat.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with tortilla chips.
Layer cut-up chicken, chopped chiles, chopped onion and grated cheeses.
Heat soups and enchilada sauce and pour over contents in pan; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Place the drained pineapple in a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Combine the flour and sugar and pour over the pineapple. Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Sprinkle the cracker crumbs on top of the cheese.
Pour the melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juice.
Stir into juice the Tang and pudding mix.
Add the fruit to mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: simple angel food cake dessert
directions: Use a deep dish glass bowl.
Slice angel food cake vertically in 3 slices.
Place bottom slice in bowl.
Cover cake with layer of pudding and add a few strawberries.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat 1/2 to 3/4-inch oil in skillet to 375°.
Beat egg; add milk.
Combine sugar, baking powder and flour.
Add egg and milk mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Use funnel cake pitcher or regular funnel, pouring batter into oil, making swirls from the center, out.
Fry until golden; turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Add additional milk if batter begins to thicken.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan or Dutch oven.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: wilted lettuce with franks
directions: Saute bacon until crisp; add franks.
Saute until brown.
Add bacon and franks to lettuce in salad bowl.
Return 3 to 4 tablespoons grease to skillet; add vinegar, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard.
Bring to boil.
Stir well and pour over lettuce until coated.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and stir together.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven until browned lightly, fluffy and firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie crust.
Place other pie crust on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large bowl (microwave is fine).
Mix margarine with grated carrots.
Microwave for about 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Toss in stuffing until moistened.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients; season lightly (salt, pepper, garlic salt).
I cook the 1/2 onion (chopped) with the squash.
Layer stuffing and other mixture in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover for the first 30 minutes; uncover remaining 10 minutes.

title: cajun jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage and onions into small pieces. Brown hamburger, sausage and onion in heavy Dutch oven; drain off grease. Dissolve bouillon in 1 cup boiling water. Add bouillon stock and remaining water to meat mixture (2 cups water for each cup of rice). Add 1 teaspoon salt for each cup of rice, 1 teaspoon Tony's Creole seasoning, a dash of Worcestershire sauce, black pepper, cayenne pepper and garlic powder to taste. Bring to a rolling boil, then turn down and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Add rice and bring to a hard boil.	Turn burner down and stir well. Place lid on tightly and cook until rice is done.

title: key largo lime pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Whisk in sugar, lime juice, egg yolks, eggs and lime peel; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in coloring.
Let cool to room temperature and pour into pie shell.
Top with toasted coconut.

title: chicken sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sprinkle onion, herbs and 2 tablespoons water on bottom of shallow baking pan.
Arrange chicken on top. Cut sausage into 1-inch diagonal slices and place on chicken. Bake for 45 minutes, uncovered, turning sausage once and basting with pan juices.
(Don't eat all the sausage before you get it to the table!) Serves 6.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease deep dish pie pan. Cook hamburg and onion. Drain.
Add seasoning to mix.
Put in pie pan and top with chilies.
Put milk, eggs and Bisquick in blender until smooth. Pour over hamburg in pie pan. Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more until knife comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese (optional).

title: apricot glaze for chicken
directions: Puree apricots.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook (bake) chicken pieces halfway, then baste twice with glaze before serving.

title: fancy chocolate candy
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in all ingredients, except chocolate and wax.
Make balls.
Cool.
In double boiler, mix chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Use toothpick and dip the balls into chocolate mixture.
Store in airtight container.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin. Fold in chocolate chips.
Place into 6 mini bread pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding, peanut butter and Cool Whip until blended and pour into pie crusts.
Drizzle with shell coating and freeze. Serve slightly thawed.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Place spices in a cheesecloth bag and bring cider, sugar and spices to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes and remove bag of spices. Keep hot but not boiling.
Makes 20 to 24 cups.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in a lightly greased 3-quart casserole. Spoon vegetables over rice.
Pour chicken broth and water over the vegetables.
Cook sausage until browned; drain well.
Spoon sausage over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and stir well.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Garnish with a mushroom and parsley, if desired.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Cream egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar. Add flour, cocoa and vanilla. Whip egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold whites in. Pour into baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Roll on dish towel and cool.
Whip the whipping cream. Sweeten to taste.
Place on cake and roll.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: champagne
directions: Follow directions on juice can, using flavored carbonated water instead of tap water.
Keep in bottle or jar with a tight fitting lid so bubbles won't disappear.
Makes four 6 ounce servings.

title: broccoli supreme casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and salt according to directions on bag; drain. Add soup, mayonnaise and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Add eggs and onion.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle grated cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
It's done when knife comes out clean.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt together, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; stir 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter with granulated and brown sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; blend into the creamed mixture to make a smooth dough.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and season to taste.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening.
Mix in with fork.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Roll out very thin on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate tops, if desired.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a graham cracker pie crust.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate before eating.

title: salsa strips
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 4 rectangles. Place on a greased baking sheet. Spread mustard and salsa on each rectangle. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until golden brown. Cool for 10 minutes. Cut each into 4 strips. Sprinkle with parsley. Yield: 16 appetizers.

title: ranch style watermelon rind preserves
directions: Cut green skin and pink flesh from thick watermelon rind.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
In large porcelain pot, cover rind with sugar at a ratio of 1 part sugar to 2 parts rind.
Let stand 4 hours. Rind will shrink and make a lot of juice.
Bring to a boil and simmer until rind is translucent (may take 4 hours).
Stir frequently to prevent sticking and burning.
Let stand 24 to 36 hours.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, until liquid reaches consistency of syrup, but still covers fruit.
While still simmering, pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix well together.
Don't add all the buttermilk at one time. Add to desired consistency.
Keep in a jar with a tight fitting lid.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans; press into 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix both puddings and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with rest of Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.	Keep refrigerated.

title: hot dip
directions: Layer ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serve with corn chips.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, blend all cake ingredients at low speed until moistened. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 70 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix ingredients together and freeze 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4 inch using rolling pin.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Swiss cheese in center of each chicken piece.
Sprinkle centers with chopped parsley.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip each chicken breast in milk; roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in baking dish coated with spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from vegetables.
Layer first 5 ingredients (in order given) in buttered casserole dish.
In a separate bowl mix celery soup, sour cream and butter.
Spread mixture on top of layered vegetables and top with crumbled Ritz crackers or stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cole slaw for freezer
directions: Let cabbage and salt set for 1 hour, then drain off water. Boil water, sugar and vinegar; let cool, then put pepper, carrots and celery seed.
Mix all ingredients well, then put in freezer.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind the fruit
ingredients
together, and then mix in sugar.

title: swedish ham slices
directions: Marinate ham slices in wine (covered) for a few hours.
Mix cream, curry powder and chilli sauce together.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: date refrigerator pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water in a saucepan and cook over slow heat until thick (about 10 minutes).
Add the nuts and cool. Meanwhile, work the shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, then add the remaining ingredients, sifted together.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Divide the mixture into two parts and roll into rectangle 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with date filling and roll up as for a jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly (overnight if possible).
Cut with sharp knife 1/4 inch thick. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour milk over bran and set aside.
Mix other ingredients and add bran.
Rest 12 hours.
Put into muffin pan without stirring batter.
Bake at 375°
for 25 minutes.

title: plum cake(apple or peach cake)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in soft margarine.
Combine egg and milk and add to dry ingredients. Mix to soft dough.
Spread in greased 13 x9-inch Pyrex pan.

title: fruit soup
directions: Combine in blender and serve chilled.
If it seems too thick, add water as needed.

title: whipped cream fruit tarts
directions: In small mixing bowl, with mixer on high, beat heavy cream until soft peaks form.

Slowly add honey. Continue to beat until stiff peaks form. Fill each tart shell 3/4 full with whipped cream mixture. With melon baller, scoop out honeydew and cantaloupe into balls. Decorate tops of tarts with melon balls and cut strawberries.
Brush with currant jelly to glaze.
Serve immediately.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir oleo, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: hamburger florentine casserole
directions: Partially fry ground beef and pour off fat.
Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Place thawed spinach in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add mushrooms and meat.
Mix soup, sour cream and rice; spread over meat.
Top with cheese. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place 2 broccoli stems beneath each chicken breast.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In a large bowl mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Put in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add hot water and stir.

title: beef and vegetable chowder
directions: Heat butter in 4 to 5 quart Dutch oven over medium-low heat. Add onions, garlic and ground beef.
Saute until brown about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes breaking into smaller pieces as you stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls and top with cheese toast.

title: green and white lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup
sugar
6 times; set aside.
Beat egg whites and salt until frothy.
Add cream of tartar; beat to peak. Fold in sugar a little
at
a time; add flavoring.
Fold in flour and sugar mixture
very gently.
Do not overmix.
Bake in
greased tube pan for
minutes
at
Invert
until completely cool.
Loosen with knife.

title: pizza
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, Crisco and milk together to make dough.
Mix tomato paste with seasonings and pour over dough. Top sauce with ground beef and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge ice cream sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients (except vanilla) in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture boils.
Add vanilla.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Stir in apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients above together, keeping them finely chopped so it is easier to spread.
Spread on flour tortillas. Roll them up and chill them in the refrigerator a few hours. Slice right before serving in bite-size pieces.
Makes approximately 50 to 60 roll-ups.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute.
Beat yolks; gradually add some hot mixture into yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook, while stirring, for 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour.
Cool. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: buttermilk ranch pretzels
directions: Break up pretzels; put in bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients;
pour over
pretzels.	Mix
well.
Place pretzels on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir occasionally.

title: nana nelson's sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: israeli chicken
directions: Mix mustard and oil.
Place chicken pieces in a baking pan. Brush with mustard mixture.
Sprinkle with seasonings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla to the mixture and stir.
Pour oatmeal in, then drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet and cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chunky guacamole
directions: Coarsely mash avocado.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Spoon into a serving bowl and serve immediately with unsalted tortilla chips.
Yield:
2 cups.
Serving size:
1 tablespoon (27 calories per serving).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cooking oil and vinegar.
Sift cake flour and soda together.
Add flour mixture.
Add buttermilk slowly.
Add vanilla and food coloring and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 3 cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic sugarless cake
directions: Boil dates and water together for 5 minutes on low.
Remove from heat; add cocoa, margarine and grated apples.
Mix well and let cool.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until it tests done.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended. Add pimento, green pepper, onion and seasoning.
Mix well.
Chill. Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, eggs and Crisco together.
Add oats, flour, chocolate chips and vanilla; mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: refrigerator cucumber-pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate in covered dish overnight. Keep refrigerated.
Yields 4 cups.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put milk in a large pan, placed in a larger kettle of water (to prevent milk scorching).
Bring milk to boiling point.
Have ready well beaten egg yolks to which sugar has been added.
Stir egg yolks into the boiling milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture is slightly thick and coats a silver spoon.
Turn off heat and immediately fold in well beaten egg whites to which a pinch of salt was added.
You may pour hot custard over the whites or fold them in.
Just be sure you do not stir.
Add vanilla.
Chill thoroughly before serving, 1 or 2 days is best.
Pecan or fruit cake is a tasty companion.

title: sage and red currant gravy
directions: Make turkey giblet stock by coarsely chopping vegetables and bringing the celery rib, carrot, onion, chicken broth, water, reserved neck and giblets, bay leaf and mixed fresh herbs to a boil. Skim froth. Simmer 2 hours or until liquid is reduced to about 6 cups. Pour stock through a fine sieve into a bowl. Complete Sage and Red Currant Gravy by combining the pan juices from the chicken or turkey, turkey giblet stock, currant jelly, sage leaves, water and cornstarch.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread little mustard on bread and cut into little squares. Place squares in buttered dish; add kraut, corned beef, soup and water.
Put Swiss cheese on top.
Microwave for 15 minutes.

title: hasselback potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes.
Put potatoes in pan of cold water; bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 450°.
Spray an ovenproof dish with Pam.
Drain potatoes.
Place slices in dish.
Sprinkle with Molly McButter.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Add water before baking, basting occasionally.
Mix Parmesan cheese with crumbs; scatter over potatoes.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine seasoning and vinegar and boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Heat to simmering and pack hot in hot jars.
Be careful to avoid boiling as that makes pickles soft.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine soup, milk and onion.
In a buttered casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, soup mixture and cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Add all other ingredients and blend.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Place thin slice of Swiss cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Mix together cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: garlic cheese toast
directions: Mix soft butter and Parmesan cheese together.
Stir in garlic powder to taste and spread on Texas toast.
Fry on both sides on solid grill or iron skillet.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: *Add 1 tablespoon vinegar in your milk to sour it.

title: cranapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until completely separated.
Mix applesauce in and stir thoroughly.
Refrigerate until set.
Can be used in jello mold.

title: chocolate pecan angels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chips, pecans and powdered sugar in medium bowl.
Add egg white; mix well.

title: icing for red velvet cake
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick, stirring constantly so it won't scorch.
Cool.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add to flour mixture and beat until fluffy.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
It will look like whipped cream.
Spread on layers.

title: jalapeno chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet, in salad oil, cook chilies, onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in cumin and cook 1 minute. Stir in soup, salt and spinach and break up spinach with a fork.
Cover and simmer until spinach is cooked.
Stir in chicken and sour cream and heat through.

title: texas cheese and artichoke spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (keep hot). Spread on cracker while hot.

title: arnold's dressing
directions: Slightly beat egg yolks, salt and pepper. Add vinegar. Cook until thick over medium heat. Good over cabbage slaw.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put cheese in crock-pot and add fried sausage and hamburger. The longer it is heated, the spicier it is.
Serve it with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or 1 large and 3 small pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness with dry toothpick.

title: double batch freeze ahead buttercream frosting
directions: Whip butter.
Gradually add sugar and flavoring.
Freeze in smaller containers.
Frost 2 cakes.
We spread on graham crackers.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Dissolve gelatin as usual.
Put in shallow pan.
When set, cut in 1/2-inch squares.
Fold into whipped cream.
Add pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Should set 12 hours.

title: almond sweet potato puffs
directions: Combine mashed potatoes with melted butter, marmalade, egg and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth; chill.
Spread almonds on sheet of waxed paper; drop potato mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls onto almonds; roll to coat on all sides.
Shape into 2-inch balls and place in greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until hot.
Place a dollop of butter and a sprig of parsley, if you wish, on each puff before serving.
Yields about 12.

title: cinnamon swirl oatmeal bread
directions: Put oatmeal, sugar, salt and butter in a large bowl.
Pour 2 cups boiling water in bowl; stir and let sit until lukewarm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake according to directions for sugar cookies on package.
Mix cream cheese with Cool Whip and spread on top of cooled cookie dough.

title: can't fail cheeseburger and fries
directions: Sit in favorite chair.
Pick up phone and call 743-7500.
Place order for cheeseburger and French fries with brown salt.
Hang up phone.
Put on shoes and walk to car.
Drive safely to Engle's Road Side Restaurant.

title: sand tarts
directions: Rub butter into flour.
Mix sugar in well.
Add eggs.
Work until well mixed.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and coat with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and chopped almonds.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt bars; pour in nuts and marshmallows.
Pour in pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: pickled fish(great with suckers, but other fish can be used.)
directions: Fillet fish and remove skin.
Cut into small pieces.
Cover pieces in brine of 1 c. pickling salt per 1 qt. water.
Soak 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Keep refrigerated.
Pour off brine, cover fish with white vinegar, soak 24 hours.
Stir occasionally and keep in refrigerator.
Pour off vinegar.
Make enough of this next mixture to cover fish:
2 c. fresh white vinegar, 4 tsp. pickling spices and 1 3/4 c. sugar.
Soak 12 hours in refrigerator, stirring occasionally.
Separate fish from liquid, keeping fish cold.
Save this liquid and boil for 15 minutes.
Cool it, then put it back on fish.
Add sliced onions and lemon juice (about 2 Tbsp.).
Wait a few days before eating.

title: my mom's pizzelle
directions: Mix the night before.
Leave in refrigerator.
Put to room temperature when ready to make.
Preheat pizzelle iron.
Put very small amount of oil on iron. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls.
Hold closed for 30 to 35 seconds for golden brown pizzelle.

title: pumpkin pie(serves 8)
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan, which has been coated with butter and flour.
This will serve as a crust for the pumpkin filling.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Chill and serve with whipped cream or nondairy whipped topping.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Boil mixture for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix and drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Let firm up, then serve.

title: mama's shortcake
directions: Simmer milk and butter.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in hot milk mixture and blend well.
Grease and flour a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serve with fruit.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Split a bean lengthwise and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Store in bottle of vodka or rum and let it sit in a dark spot (in a cupboard) for at least 6 weeks.
The longer you let the beans marinate, the stronger the flavor will be.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli five minutes and drain.
Mix all together and put in a greased casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for thirty minutes.
Easy!
Easy! Easy!

title: jello salad
directions: Bring jello,
sugar and crushed pineapple to a boil and cool. Add
nuts, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix together. Pour in dish and let chill.

title: honey lemon carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Immerse carrots and scallions in boiling, salted water and cook until tender-crisp.
Place in cold water to stop cooking and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients. Vary the proportions according to sweetness of carrots.
Place carrots and scallions in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them and bake for 15 minutes.

title: stuffaroni
directions: Brown crumbled sausage.
Add marinara sauce and water; bring to a boil.
Combine Ricotta, Parmesan, cheese, egg and green pepper.
Fill cooked stuffaroni with mixture.
Make single layer in pan.
Top with sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: goo cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, 1 stick butter melted and press in a 9 x 13 in. pan.
Then mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and 1 lb of confectioners sugar.
Pour on top of crust.
Then sprinkle 1 cup of pecans (chopped) on top.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour or until brown on top.
Must be completely cooled before cutting.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator to develop flavor.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer until fluffy. Add oatmeal, flour and then cornflakes.
(I add chocolate chips, too!)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese well with electric mixer.
Slowly add milk and blend until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Spread pie filling over top.

title: lumpiang shanghai
directions: Combine pork, carrots, 1 beaten egg, sesame oil, green onions, water chestnuts and salt.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of the mixture on each lumpia wrapper.
Roll the wrapper and seal with mixture of one egg and 2 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Deep fry, then cut into 3 pieces.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce or catsup.

title: burger bundles
directions: Combine 1 pound ground beef mixed with 1/2 cup milk.
Flatten into patties.
Place stuffing in center of patty and pull meat up around the stuffing.
Place on a cookie sheet and pour over the following (heated until bubbly): mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Bake uncovered in oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 5.

title: "best chops around"
directions: Place 4 or 5 center cut pork chops in heavy foil.
Mix apricot preserves with Russian dressing, about 1/2 of Lipton onion soup mix and about 1 cup golden raisins.
Close foil; cook about 40 minutes at 325° or until tender.

title: zucchini spaghetti
directions: Salt zucchini and onion in 2 tablespoons of oil; when half-done, add can of chopped tomatoes and juice.
When liquid is hot, add broken up spaghetti to liquid (nice handful).
Cook until done (stir often).
Add Parmesan cheese to each serving.
Leftover sausage, pork and chicken can be added at the last 3 minutes cooking time.

title: chili casserole
directions: Combine chili, corn and onion.
Place in casserole dish.
Add cheese.
Spoon muffin mix on top.
(Muffin mix is to be mixed as to directions on box.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and stuffing mix. Saute onions until soft in oil. Add to other ingredients. Put in greased casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: italian zucchini  crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano leaves.
Combine eggs and cheese in mixing bowl.
Stir in zucchini mixture.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Brown onion and ground beef together.
Pour rest of ingredients into crock-pot. Add ground beef-onion mixture.
Crumble bacon into it.
Cook on low until heated through.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together three times 2 cups plain flour, cocoa and 1/2 teaspoon salt and set aside.
Mix together buttermilk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and red food coloring and beat well.
Add flour mixture and milk mixture alternately to shortening and sugar mixture.
Mix soda in vinegar and mix into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern catfish stew
directions: Simmer fish in 6-quart pan with enough water to cover fish. Cook for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove fish from broth and bone.
Fry pork until brown.
Place fish, pork, onion and potatoes in broth. Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: baked cocktail franks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter with mustard in a small bowl; mix well.
Unroll rolls; separate into 4 rectangular pieces. Pinch together to make dough solid.
Spread butter mixture on dough.
Cut into 6 strips.
Place Smokie on end of each strip. Roll up and pinch to seal.
Place sealed side down on greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg yolk with water; brush on rolls.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions. Crush potato chips. Add 1 1/2 cups water to cream of chicken soup and mix well. In an 8 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish, layer bottom with onions. Pour a layer of potato chips. Continue layers until dish is full. Pour all soup mixture over top. Cover and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until onions are tender. Remove from oven and cover top with cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: krinkle sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in the last 4 ingredients.
Roll teaspoons of dough in sugar (or cinnamon sugar) and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook peeled and diced potatoes in boiling, salted water. Drain. Mash until smooth.
Add
remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Cover and
place
in
refrigerator
or use.
To serve:
Place desired amount in casserole dish;
dot with butter.
Heat at 300° until warm through.

title: luscious layers
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Place sliced potatoes in bottom of a 2 1/2-quart nonstick baking dish. Alternate layers of carrot, rice, onion mixture and zucchini. Stir seasonings into mashed tomatoes and pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 8.
Contains 97 calories per serving and 1 gram fat.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Beat egg and add other ingredients.
Roll teaspoon of batter in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: chocolate cherry fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using solid shortening or margarine (not oil), grease and flour 15x10-inch jelly roll pan or 13x9-inch pan. In large bowl, combine ingredients.
By hand, stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20-30 minutes (for jelly roll pan) or 25-30 min. for 13x9-inch pan or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Press with sugared glass and bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet until light brown, approximately 15 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing(low calorie)
directions: Mix all together and blend well.

title: pepper cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Stir in cheese, onions and pepper.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: creamy garlic salad dressing
directions: Put minced garlic, 1/3 of the sour cream, oil, vinegar, herbs and mayonnaise in blender and mix at high speed.
(Use hand mixer if no blender.)
Empty blended contents into a bowl and add remaining sour cream.
Blend with a wooden spoon just until well mixed.
Chill if desired.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set remaining batter aside. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt caramels, milk and butter together.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle baked part of cake with chocolate chips, pour caramel mix over that, then pour remaining cake batter on the top.
Return pan to oven; bake another 20 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: ma's carrot cupcakes
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar together in a bowl.
Add rest of ingredients until blended well.
Fill cupcake pans, lined with cupcake papers, 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tops are browned.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pasta salad
directions: Rinse cooked spaghetti under cold water; toss with oil to prevent sticking.
Prepare vegetables as follows (food processors are helpful):
Shred the carrots, julienne cut (3 x 3 mm) the red bell pepper and zucchini and slice thinly the celery.
Shred the low-fat Cheddar cheese.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in oblong pan.
Beat together vanilla pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Put mixture on top of baked cake. Add drained, crushed pineapple and pat into the pudding mixture. Before serving, top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: caramel nut fudge
directions: Mix all together and bring to a full boil.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir until it thickens or loses some of the gloss.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Pour pie filling into 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix from the entire box on top.
Spread melted butter on top of this and bake in a 375° oven until brown and bubbly, 45 minutes or longer.
Serve warm or cool, plain or with ice cream, milk or whipped cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In small saucepan cook sugar and water to soft ball stage (234° to 240°).
Add raw peanuts, continue cooking until syrup is light brown and meets hard crack test (300° to 310°).

title: pork in lime cream sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat oil in heavy ovenproof skillet over high heat.
Add pork and brown on all sides, turning frequently.
Transfer skillet with pork to oven and roast pork about 20 minutes, until done.

title: salsa, for flavor
directions: Place all ingredients in a large jar with a lid.
Shake until well mixed.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with corn chips, over vegetables or as a sauce on top of a Mexican dish. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate cake frosting
directions: Mix well.
Pour over cake while cake is hot.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Slice oranges and lemon.
Remove seeds.
For every pound of fruit, add 3 pints of water and set away for 24 hours.
Boil until tender, then set away for another 24 hours.

title: canoli shells
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and creme de cacao.
Add Hershey bar and cherries.
Stir all together and fill shells.

title: caramel icing(3 layers)
directions: Mix sugar (3 cups), flour and salt; add milk and butter. Bring to a boil.
Add the 1/2 cup sugar which has been caramelized in a small heavy pan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla. Beat.
If icing gets too stiff, add a few drops of milk.

title: sourdough rye bread
directions: Take a ball (1.5-inch diameter) of starter.
Add 1/2 cup lukewarm water and 2 tablespoons rye flour.
Mash with a fork until well blended.
Set aside in a warm place to allow the sponge to start. The degree of sourness depends on the length of time this is allowed to stand.
Minimum is about 12 hours and maximum about 24 hours.

title: cheese crunchers
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and butter together; stir in graham cracker crumbs and walnuts until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafood appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Garnish with parsley or other greens.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons margarine and cornstarch; cook gently. Remove from heat; stir in seasonings and sour cream.
Fold in beans.
Place in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Three slices bacon, fried crisp and drained, may be added to this if you so desire just before baking.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread cubes.
Pile lightly into baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated Old English cheese and toasted bread cubes.
Bake until bubbly, at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grandmother's pinto beans
directions: Place pinto beans, water, bacon drippings and salt in a large pot; bring to a rapid boil for 20 minutes.
Turn heat off.
Place lid on pot and let sit for 30 minutes.
Turn heat on and bring to a rapid boil.
Turn heat down to medium boil.
In 1 hour, add paprika.
Cook beans until they are soft, about 1 1/2 hours. Remove lid and boil rapidly until juice thickens, stirring as juice is boiling.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Toss the chocolate chips in 1 tablespoon of the dry cake mix. Beat the remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes, then fold in the chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake 50 minutes at 350° or until cake tests clean.
Makes 10 servings.

title: barbecue shrimp (microwave)
directions: Cook in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour over washed, deheaded shrimp (enough sauce for about 2 pounds of large shrimp).
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Serve with French bread for dunking in the sauce.

title: crispy chicken livers
directions: In skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble; set aside.
Cut chicken livers in half.
In small mixing bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip livers in flour mixture. Turn to coat.

In skillet, brown livers in bacon drippings over medium heat, turning occasionally, until livers are brown and crispy on the exterior and cooked thoroughly, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: lemon filling
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, add water, egg yolk and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Once thick, remove from heat. Add lemon peel and butter. Cool before spreading on cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately; beat well.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and approximately 25 minutes.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 325°.
Start timer after cake is put in oven.
Let cool in pan.
Do not open oven door while baking.
It will fall.
Test cake after 1 hour and 25 minutes. Bottom of pan may be lined with wax paper.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In a saucepan, heat together chili, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Stir to blend and melt cheeses.
Serve warm with chips.

title: peanut butter chocolate chips cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and all sugars.
Add peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Batter gets really stiff, so mix with hands. Take small pieces, roll into a ball, place on greased cookie sheet, mash down with fork both ways.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes and beat in the ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Keep in refrigerator until needed (can be made several days ahead).
Bake in low oven until warmed through (1 hour or so).

title: stuffed pistolettes
directions: Brown ground beef, or mix cooked chicken, shrimp or crawfish with onion. Cook broccoli according to directions on box. Combine meat and broccoli; add cheese and stir until mixed. Cut small circle off top of roll and clean out most of the inside; mix 2 cups of the bread pieces with the meat mix. Fill each roll with mixture and replace circle of bread to cover top. Melt margarine and garlic salt; roll each roll in it after filling it. Put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mexican cold soup
directions: Simmer the first 6 ingredients for 15 minutes.
When cold, add vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Also great with Tabasco sauce and/or leftover crab meat.

title: chinese oriental salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and add noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds.
Stir to coat.
Spread on cookie sheet and brown in oven (can be done ahead).

title: heavenly salad
directions: Drain all fruit well. Mix well, chill and serve.

title: black beans and corn combo
directions: Heat oil in a large, non-stick skillet over medium heat.
Add onions, carrots, celery, and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender, adding small amounts of water as necessary to prevent drying.
Reduce heat to low.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Beat eggs, salt, dry mustard and milk. Layer bread, cubed meat and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake in morning at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Prepare batter of egg, water, flour and salt and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Heat oil in wok.
Dip pork in batter and fry a few pieces at a time.
Drain.
Stir-fry vegetables in a small amount of oil (2 tablespoons).
Combine brown sugar, vinegar, juice, water, soy and cornstarch until mixed.
Add to vegetables in wok and heat.
Add pineapple chunks and heat until sauce thickens. Pour over pork and rice and serve at once.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Drain crab, shrimp and clams, reserving liquids.
Slice crab with sharp knife.
Cook bacon and garlic in large saucepan until bacon is crisp.
Add potatoes and reserved liquids from seafood, wine, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add crab, shrimp, clams, corn, milk, half and half, onion and parsley.
Heat to simmer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Stir in butter and chocolate.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Spoon into greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool, serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Slice
onion
thin;
add
salt with a little water.
In salad bowl,
combine
ingredients to make dressing; mix well. Add tomatoes, cucumbers and onion; coat well.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 3 layers according to directions on box.
Mix chocolate pudding, yogurt and 1/3 cup of the milk.
Stir and add remaining 2/3 cup milk and beat two minutes.
Spread between layers and
top with Cool Whip and almond slices.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 quart saucepan.
Drain juice from pineapple (save pineapple tidbits), add water to make one cup.
Mix with sugar and cornstarch.
Turn on heat to medium.
Stir.
Add vinegar, ketchup and pineapple.
Stir, bring to low boil.

title: curry cheese dip
directions: Blend with mixer and refrigerate.
Serve with any type of crackers.

title: hot chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
In
saucepan combine oil, cocoa, butter and water.
Bring to a
boil.
Add this to flour mixture. Add
baking soda and buttermilk.
Beat eggs slightly and add
to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13
x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Combine hot water and sugar; boil.
Remove from heat; add jello mixture, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Pour into plastic gallon containers and freeze.
Remove punch from freezer 8 hours before it is to be served.
Pour into punch bowl when ready to serve; add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Serves 70 to 75.

title: oyster cracker bridge mix
directions: In brown bag, mix all ingredients, except corn oil.
Shake. Next pour corn oil over ingredients and shake.
Store in an airtight container.
Better if made a couple of days ahead before serving.
Good.

title: broccoflower beef
directions: *Ground beef makes a flavorful substitute.

title: mama artie's cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in bowl. Add beaten egg and milk.
Pour into a preheated iron skillet greased with 1 tablespoon oil.
Bake in 450° oven until brown.

title: chicken lasagna(cook 1 hour at 425.)
directions: Mix cottage cheese and eggs together. Cook chicken breast with garlic, mushrooms, and a little olive oil. Cook noodles until they are almost done. Layer ingredients as follows, 1/4 jar sauce enough to cover pan bottom, noodles, rest of jar of sauce, 1/2 of chicken, 1/2 of cottage cheese and egg mixture,1/2 of all cheeses, 1/2 can parmesan cheese, layer of noodles. Repeat layers as above. Cook for 1 hour at 425 degrees.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Dip fillets in beaten egg.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In the bottom of a large bowl place 1/2 of the head of lettuce, torn into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle with a dash of sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer the eggs on top of the lettuce. Next layer in order peas, remaining lettuce (also torn in bite size pieces), bacon and cheese.
Spread salad dressing over the top.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add potatoes and mix.
Add lemon juice, thyme and salt.
Oil baking dish, put half of mixture in dish and sprinkle with flour.
Add rest of mixture.
Pour in skim milk and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple sticky buns
