directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until well blended.
Divide among 12 large muffin cups.
Set aside.
Mix last 3 ingredients together until just moist.
Drop batter on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert on rack immediately to prevent sticking.

title: honey-apple pancakes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt, apple pie spice and baking soda.
In a small bowl, stir together egg, apple juice, honey and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring until blended but still slightly lumpy. (If you want a thinner batter, add a little more apple juice.)

title: breakfast bake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Sprinkle in croutons, cheese, onions, pepper, mushrooms and meat. In a bowl, combine the eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Mix well and pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: oatmeal toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended.
Add oats, Bits 'O Brickle, coconut and nuts.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spread on a "jelly roll" pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: curried apricots
directions: Arrange drained apricot halves in a pie plate.
Spoon the combined butter, sugar and curry powder over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
This is delicious served with a chicken dish.

title: orange apple punch
directions: Combine to make 20 cups.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Stir and let boil 2 minutes.
Beat 2 eggs and add to slightly cooled date mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon salt. Boil 2 minutes more while stirring.
Take off stove and add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup Rice Krispies, slightly crushed.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage for about 10 minutes; remove.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Add peppers, onion, garlic and oregano. Saute until tender-crisp.
Add broth and sausage.
Cook until heated.
Add noodles.
Toss to coat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham apollo
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender; blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Stir in ham and 1/2 cup cheese.
Alternate layers of noodles and sauce mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with additional cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter; add sugar and beat well. Add eggs and vanilla, beat until fluffy.
Sift flour, measure; add salt, soda and baking powder; sift again.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator.
(I don't always do this.)
Shape dough into balls 1 inch in diameter. (I use the small Pampered Chef scoop.)
Place 2-3 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.	Remove and press a chocolate kiss in center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake for 4 minutes more.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup.
Place in baking pan in a loaf.
Top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Pour cider into large saucepan; add spices and salt and cover. Bring slowly to boiling point.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in Sweeta; remove from heat.
Serve at once in mugs garnished with additional cinnamon sticks.
Serves 12.

title: pecan roll
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add milk to mixture.
Stir in crumbs and pecans.
Roll out in a log shape on buttered wax paper. Store in refrigerator.
Slice as needed.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until red color leaves.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add water; dissolve gravy mix.
Add one layer of sliced carrots, one layer of onions and add sliced potatoes.
Cook at 350° until potatoes are tender.
Put layer of grated cheese on and put back in oven to melt.

title: oriental chicken broccoli
directions: In skillet, heat oil and cook chicken until brown.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken (skin can be removed).
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients, then roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange in single layer in same pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange chocolate chippers
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, orange peel and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend together flour and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Using reserved broth, cook noodles.
Stir together chicken, noodles, sour cream, milk, soup, salt, pepper and parsley.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Ritz crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 40 minutes.

title: window cleaner
directions: Mix in a bucket of warm water.

title: christmas pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Coat nuts and cherries with small portion of the flour.
Stir remaining flour into creamed mixture. Add nuts, cherries and coconut; mix well.
Turn into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Pour the boiling water over poppy seed and let stand 1/2 hour. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: mamaw smith's fresh coconut cake
directions: Beat eggs whites first, add 1/4 of sugar, then beat egg yolks; add
milk	to
egg
yolks.
Add sugar, then add melted oleo, then
add
flour to batter.
Add vanilla and egg whites last. Bake at 325° until cake springs back to touch.

title: french dressing i
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Pour in bottles and refrigerate.

title: soft pretzels or breadsticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar and salt.
Add flour; blend flour until smooth and form shapes.
Place on greased baking sheet; brush with egg.
Sprinkle toppings (salt, seeds, etc.). Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix together in container with tight cover. Combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over beans and again mix well.
Store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours, shaking bowl whenever you think about it.
Serve cold.
Will remain fresh in refrigerator for 7 to 10 days if kept sealed.

title: day ahead shrimp paste
directions: Mix soup and cream cheese until very smooth over medium heat. Mix gelatine and water and add.
Mix rest of ingredients and fold all together.
Mold in jello mold or bowl.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
To unmold, place in warm water a few seconds.

title: golden gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and salt; stir, then add shredded carrot and pineapple. Refrigerate until set.

title: prize-winning cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients, then add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Drop and bake at 400°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, mix in milk and butter.
Chop corn in food processor; add corn, sugar, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Grease baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Add water and chocolate.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: double peanut cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In hot oven, melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove.
Stir in crumbs; spread evenly on bottom.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with a layer of peanut butter chips, a layer of chocolate pieces and then the peanuts.
Press peanuts gently into mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes or until edges are brown.
Chill 1 hour before cutting into bars.

title: garden fresh stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add green pepper and water; mix lightly.
Cover; cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in mushrooms; continue cooking 10 minutes.
Heat cream cheese and milk over low heat; stir until smooth.
Stir in onion and onion salt; heat thoroughly.
Spoon meat mixture over noodles; top with cream cheese sauce.
Garnish with additional green onion slices, if desired.

title: tijuana meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper, carrots, onion and eggs.
Pack into a 2-quart loaf pan.

title: spinach soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until soft.
Clean from bones and chop fine.
Cook spinach, drain and chop fine.
Beat eggs well, stir in cheese and spinach.
Place chopped chicken in broth.
When boiling, stir in egg mixture.
Cook a few minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni (salt).
Beat egg.
Add milk and water and cut up cheese.
Mix with hot macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cook until cheese is melted and egg is done.
Pour in dish and put a few pieces of cheese on top and boil until cheese is melted.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook veggies in butter until tender but not brown.
Stir flour into broth until smooth.
Add broth and cream to vegetables.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook just until cheese is melted. Serves 4.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter, then cover.
Mix other ingredients and add to butter and chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip if desired before serving.
Serves 8.

title: sweet success rice pudding
directions: Place cooked rice, milk and sugar in medium heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium to high heat.
Reduce heat to medium; simmer until thick and creamy, while stirring frequently, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into medium bowl.
Stir in vanilla, cinnamon and raisins.
Cool in refrigerator until firm. Serve with topping garnish.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue ribs on grill
directions: Place ribs in foil pan.
Pour can of beer over ribs.
Pour barbecue sauce over beer and ribs.
Cover with foil and cook about 1 hour.
Take ribs out of pan and brown on grill.
Put back in pan and bake until real tender, 1/2 to 1 hour longer.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Combine Italian dressing, vinegar and water.
Let stand for 2 minutes, then add mayonnaise and stir.

title: chicken pie
directions: Simmer chicken in water until done.
Skin, bone and cut into pieces.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
*Boil broth and soup together and pour over chicken.
Make batter of flour, margarine, buttermilk and pepper.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meringue crusted pie
directions: Set oven at 300°.
Beat together first 4 ingredients until forms soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in pecans.
Spread mix onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Turn off oven and allow crust to dry in oven for 2 hours.
Cool on wire rack.

title: glenna's sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use medium size cucumbers.
Wash and cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand 4 or 5 hours.
Boil syrup for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling syrup over cucumbers in jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes (cold pack for 5 minutes).

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and mayonnaise, cheese and milk in a saucepan. Heat on low heat until cheese melts, then add chicken and vegetables.
Heat through.
Put all ingredients into a large casserole dish and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of water.
Heat to a boil.
Add can of tomato soup and cream cheese and cook until melted.
Mix in mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Pour in mold and chill until firm.

title: polk salad alice
directions: Chop all ingredients together.
Bring canola oil to sizzling hot and pour over greens.
Serve immediately with crackers.

title: chinese pork
directions: Marinate overnight in sauce.
Bake on a rack in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cut in 2-inch slices.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all except last 2 ingredients.
Spread dry breadcrumbs on waxed paper.
Shape mixture into 3-inch patties; cook 2 or 3 minutes per side.

title: mom's piccalilli
directions: Discard blossom end of tomatoes, but do not peel them.
Chop tomatoes.
(All vegetables may be put through food chopper or coarse blade of food processor.)
Combine chopped vegetables with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain thoroughly and then add the remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 1 hour or until mixture thickens.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal at once.
Makes 6 1/2-quarts or 13 pints.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Place beans in dutch oven with sausage.
Cover with water two inches above beans.
Let beans boil a few minutes, 5 to 10, then drain.
Cover with about 4 inches of water and simmer until beans are done and liquid is a little thickened, but still soupy.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour over ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or less.

title: german slaw
directions: Cut up cabbage and slice onions, then mix other ingredients, except oil.
Bring to a boil.
Pour these ingredients over cabbage, then add oil last.
Refrigerate.

title: louise's dill bread
directions: Soften the packet of yeast in warm water.
Combine cottage cheese (heated to lukewarm) and other ingredients, adding flour last, enough to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole.
Let rise in warm place until light, 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: swordfish provencale
directions: Cook tomatoes slowly in margarine and 1 tablespoon oil until they begin to get pasty.
Add parsley, basil and wine and continue cooking slowly for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and let mixture simmer, stirring occasionally.
Coat steaks with flour.
Shape large heavy skillet with Pam, then add 1 tablespoon oil.
Let pan heat slightly, then add steaks and garlic.
Cook/brown steaks on each side until done (allow 10 minutes per inch of steak thickness).
Remove and serve topped with tomato mixture.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Mix soup mix, sour cream and spinach together.
Serve with crackers.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine
sugar, water, cinnamon and allspice in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add
pecans
and continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and
add
vanilla.
Place
pecans
individually on waxed paper. Cool completely.
Yields 2 cups.

title: caramel apples
directions: Melt caramels over low heat.
Dip apples in melted caramel and place on greased wax paper.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain beans, corn, peas and mushrooms.
Place in serving dish. Slice large onion thinly and separate.
Add pimento to vegetables.

title: beefy chicken breasts
directions: Place dried beef in baking dish.
Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Wrap each with 1 slice of bacon.
Place in prepared dish.
Combine sour cream and soup in bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: apostle's favorite minestrone soup
directions: In a large soup pan, fry hamburger with onions.
Drain off fat completely.
Add 6 cups water, bouillon cubes, Prego and Veg-All. When boiling, add noodles.
Boil continuously for 8 minutes, until noodles are cooked.
Simmer on low until ready to serve.
Serve with warm Italian bread.
Enjoy!

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add 1 small box of strawberry jello and stir until dissolved.
Chill until it begins to thicken, then add fresh chopped strawberries.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm and top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small, deep bowl.
Dip chicken pieces about the size of walnuts into batter and deep fry until golden brown.
By the time they reach this color, the meat will be cooked through.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in 1 loaf pan, 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak (cut into strips) in butter.
Simmer until tender. Add mushrooms, chopped onion, celery, salt and pepper to taste. Add water.
Thicken with flour paste to desired consistency.
Stir in sour cream and horseradish.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: snoballs
directions: Drop by the teaspoons into hot fat until brown.
Drain.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together in big bowl.
Pour
into greased casserole dish; top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes
mixed	with 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
This will make 1 large casserole or 2 small ones.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 20 minutes or until the cranberry skins pop.
Cool to room temperature or chill and serve.

title: clam and cheese dunk
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in refrigerator so that flavors will blend.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cool punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and 1 gallon of water in large container; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well until sugar is dissolved.
Chill and serve.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: fudgy-wudgy cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add oil, coffee and milk. Blend thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigeration makes cake fudgier.
Ice if desired. Serves 8.

title: family reunion barbecue mustard base sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You may add or subtract any ingredient as long as the mustard remains the base for the sauce. Heat to warm and blend.
Apply liberally.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat on low speed until smooth. Chill before serving.
May be used as a spread or a dip.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together in small bowl until well blended.
Serve chilled.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; rinse in cold water.
Wash stalks of celery and dice up.
Rinse off tiny shrimp.
In large bowl, add macaroni, celery and shrimp.
Add just enough salad dressing until all mixture is coated lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked red onions
directions: Combine liquids and spices and pour over onions in an oven proof dish.
Cover.

title: fast and easy texas chili
directions: Fry hamburger in a large pot; drain.
Add remaining ingredients
and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over elbow macaroni, if desired.
Medium or mild picante sauce may be substituted.

title: no bake pidge cake with whipped cream icing
directions: Blend together ingredients.
Mix on high for 10 minutes.
Cake consists of two pieces of styrofoam any shape you desire.
Place one piece on plate and cover with icing.
Place other piece on top and spread with remaining icing.
Decorate according to occasion. Icing is great on any cake.

title: gooey cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Spread in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and 1/2 box of powdered sugar.
Spread over first layer.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Allow to cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In saucepan, add flour and butter. Cook until butter melts. Stir constantly, about 1 minute. Slowly add 1/2 cup milk and stir until it starts to thicken. Add milk until desired thickness. Then add cheese. Stir until cheese melts.

title: bachelor's chicken
directions: Put chicken in casserole dish with lid.
Mix catsup, mayonnaise and dressing together; pour mixture over chicken; put lid on; bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top of cheese mixture.
Swirl with fork or whisk.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: microwave play dough
directions: Mix together water and salt in a 2-quart measuring cup.
Bring to a boil in the microwave.
Stir every 2 minutes until salt is dissolved.
Remove from microwave; add food coloring and salad oil. In a large microwave bowl, mix 2 cups flour and alum.
Add salt-water liquid; mix well.
Add more flour, if needed, to make a ball.
Knead dough for a couple of minutes.
Cook play dough for 2 minutes in the microwave.
Knead dough.
Repeat, if necessary, cooking dough for 1 to 2 minutes while kneading dough until desired texture.
Cool completely and then store in airtight container.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with
bacon
pieces and bake 1 hour at 325°, uncovered.	Do not overbake as it tends to separate.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Prepare strawberries.
Place in pie crust and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, mix gelatin and pudding mix.
Add 2 cups water. Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly. Pour over berries just enough glaze to cover with thin layer.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla gently.
Spoon over glazed berries.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: old fashioned apple bread
directions: Mix sugars and shortening for 3 to 5 minutes on low speed of mixer.
Add water and eggs and mix.
Combine dry ingredients and add to the previous mixture gradually and mix well.
Fold in apples.
Pour batter into oblong pan which has been greased.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: soup burgers
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and peppers.
Mix catsup and soup. Pour over hamburger mixture.
Serve on buns.

title: buttermilk batter-fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/2-inch slices and separate into rings; set aside. Whisk together flour, buttermilk, sugar, baking powder and salt until smooth.

title: hamburger chop suey(a family favorite!)
directions: Brown meat and onions in large fry pan.
Drain grease.
Season with pepper, no salt!

title: thai chicken strips
directions: In food processor or blender, process Italian dressing, wine, sugar, soy sauce, coriander, ginger, cumin and paprika until blended.
In large shallow baking dish, combine dressing mixture, sesame seed and chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, at least 3 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Melt (heat until bubbles) butter. Add water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture combined soda, lemon juice and sweet milk.
Mix all.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Pour in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Ice while hot.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Place chicken in baking dish and layer noodles over chicken.
Mix together the soups and Ro-Tel and pour over noodle layer.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place Velveeta slices on top and bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: pear salad
directions: On a bed of shredded lettuce or lettuce leaves put pears, then in center of each put about 1 tablespoons cottage cheese.
Serves 6.

title: gran gran's fudge icing
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add milk.
Cook on medium temperature until soft ball stage.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Add stick of oleo and vanilla.
Beat until not runny.
(Cook like candy.)

title: pominski pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: a & w hot dog sauce
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Put on hot dogs.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix and smooth into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; fold in applesauce.
Sift flour, spices and baking soda together.
Add part of flour mixture at a time, then add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Mix well and put in tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours in preheated 325° oven (use toothpick test for doneness).
Let cool slightly, loosen sides of pan and turn out cake onto baking rack.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain Veg-All and mushrooms.
Mix all canned ingredients in a large bowl. Add cubed chicken.
Pour into one crust.
Invert other crust over it, removing tin from top crust.
Poke holes and brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ribbon meat loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, salt, pepper, onion and milk.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Fill pan with three layers of meat and 2 layers of stuffing, beginning and ending with meat.
Pack layers firmly! Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes until done; remove from pan and slice.

title: annabel's meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Then add meat and mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan lined with foil.
Spread ketchup on top of mixture and place foil over top.
Bake at 400° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In bowl, mix ground beef, egg, garlic salt, onion salt, beefy mushroom soup and rice.
Roll into small meatballs and cook.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions and sugar for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Add water, wine and broth; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cut 1-inch slices of bread. Toast in oven at 325° until lightly browned.
Ladle soup into soup bowls with 1 slice of toasted bread on top of each.
Fold cheese to fit bowls.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cabrito guisado
directions: Let meat cook in its own juices.
If not fat, add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water and steam until dry.
Add remaining ingredients (except cabrito) and let fry for a few minutes.
Thicken with flour dissolved in water.
Add cabrito until desired thickness is reached.
You may add tomato sauce if you wish.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat undrained oysters on medium in a 3 to 4-quart pot.
Cook until oysters curl around the edges (moderately shrink).
Pour in milk to make broth.
Add 2 tablespoons butter (or margarine).
Add pepper to taste.
Let heat until butter is fully melted.
Do not boil.
Stew is ready to serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: sauteed portabella mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in skillet, then when butter is hot, add mushrooms and seasonings. Great served over steak or if served over baked potato, add a small onion in saut process.

title: cinnamon treats
directions: Trim crusts off bread and roll flat with rolling pin. Beat egg yolk, cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar. Spread mixture on each slice of bread. Roll each slice tightly and dip in melted butter. Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and cinnamon. Roll each roll in it. Freeze on cookie sheet, seam side down. Bake as needed in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: lemon pineapple smoothies
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients. Cover and process until smooth. Pour into chilled glasses. Serve immediately. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat well. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until very stiff. Add almond extract and vanilla extract.
Fold in pecans and chocolate morsels. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet lined with ungreased heavy brown paper or foil.
Place in oven and turn off heat at once. Do not peek!
Leave overnight. Yields 4 dozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl; mix together.
Fold; put in pie shells.
Chill.
These pies freeze well.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart bowl.
Toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.
Serves 8.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Bring to a boil water and cooking oil.
Immediately add flour. Place in pie plate and press in place.
Cook as needed for your particular recipe.

title: special peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Dip peaches in scalding hot water for a few seconds.
Slip off skins while hot.
Stick 4 cloves in each peeled peach and place in roaster.
Mix sugar, vinegar, cinnamon sticks and allspice in a bowl.
Mix well and pour over peaches. Cover with liquid.

title: potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add all ingredients, except paprika.
Beat until combined.
Pour into a lightly buttered 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 6 hours. Remove from fridge for 15 minutes before baking.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: herb vegetable bake
directions: For herb sauce, add 1/4 teaspoon dried dill weed or basil to 1 cup medium white sauce (double recipe of sauce).
Toss sauce with ingredients.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: monkey toes
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon together.
Roll the biscuits into this mixture.
Melt butter.
Add 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Put 1/2 of coated biscuits into Bundt pan.
Spread 1/2 of syrup over them.
Put remaining coated biscuits on top of syrup and spread remaining syrup over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Don't cut; just pick apart.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk, egg and onion.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep fryer (hot oil at 375°) frying only a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 2 dozen hush puppies.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well and set aside.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crunchies(a recipe from south africa; serves 10)
directions: Melt together first 4 ingredients.
Add (already mixed together) the remaining ingredients.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut while hot (immediately) into squares and put back in oven (switched off) for about 10 minutes.
Use 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Combine chicken soup, salad dressing, curry powder, lemon juice, salt and pepper well.
Layer half the broccoli, chicken and soup mixture in a 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings and return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes until onions are hot.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender and boil broccoli until nearly done.
Blend last 4 ingredients.
Put broccoli in casserole and arrange chicken, broken in good sized pieces, on top.
Pour sauce over top and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: microwave pizza casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, microwave hamburger for 3 1/2 minutes; stir and micro another 2 1/2 minutes or until done.
Drain thoroughly; add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well; cook for 17 minutes on High, stirring twice during cooking. Sprinkle cheese over and cook 1 more minute.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: doubleday cocoa brownies(cholesterol free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; set aside.
In medium bowl of an electric mixer, beat margarine, egg whites and sugar until light and fluffy.
On wax paper combine flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Add half the flour mixture to egg mixture, mixing well.
Stir in milk until combined.
Add remaining flour mixture, mixing until well blended.
Stir in 3/4 cup cereal and the peanuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cereal.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 12 bars.

title: creamy greek potatoes
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes and place them in a baking dish. Salt and pepper to your desire.
Sprinkle Cavender's seasoning across top.

Place 1/2 margarine in patties across potatoes. Sprinkle cheese and then remaining margarine on top of the cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes depending on the thickness of the potatoes.
Makes approximately 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: banana bread
directions: * To make sour milk, mix regular milk and vinegar.

title: mom's fruit yogurt pie
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, soften gelatin in water. Cook and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Stir in yogurt. Chill until partially set (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Put the cucumbers into a stone jar, washed and sliced. Dissolve salt in the boiling water and pour over the cucumbers. Cover and pour 1 gallon boiling water.
Weight down.
Let stand 1 week.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf.
Place potatoes in bottom of crock-pot.
Top potatoes with meat loaf.
Cover and cook on low, 8 to 10 hours. Serves 6.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring butter and water to a boil.
Remove from the heat; stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, almond extract, salt and baking soda until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes or until cake is golden brown and tests done.
Cool for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, make frosting.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Spread bottom of greased casserole dish with 8 piles of dried beef.
Roll chicken breasts with strips of bacon and place on top of the beef.
Mix soups, sour cream and cream cheese.
Pour over chicken and bake about 2 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cherry dessert cup
directions: Mix, chill and serve in dessert cups.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Cook onion in oil; add salt. Cover. Cook until tender not brown. Add paprika and cook 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes and broth. Stir occasionally to break up tomatoes. Add chicken and simmer meat side down, covered, for 10 minutes. Simmer, uncovered, until chicken is cooked through, 5 to 10 more minutes. Remove chicken from sauce and keep warm.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Cut up onion, celery and green pepper.
Place these in the pot at the same time you start cooking beef.
Also add tomato paste. Cook beef for about 1 hour.
Dice potatoes.
Add potatoes and mixed vegetables to pot when beef has cooked for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to your own taste.

title: rocky road squares
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips, margarine and milk until well blended.
Combine peanuts and marshmallows and pour chocolate mixture over all.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Remove from pan, peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store at room temperature.

title: hearty lentil stew
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot oil, cook celery, carrots and onion with garlic until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 1 hour or longer until lentils are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
(Stir frequently.)

title: linda's corn fritters
directions: Mix the flour sugar, salt and baking powder in one bowl. Drain the corn, reserving about 1/4 cup of the juice.
Beat the eggs well; mix rest of ingredients, including the corn, 1/4 cup juice and milk together.
Fry in oil until done.
Try not to turn but one time on each side.

title: cindy's peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of shallow oblong baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix together 2 teaspoons flour and 1/2 cup sugar. Sprinkle this on top of peaches.
Then mix 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and 1 egg until mixture is crumbly.
Pour over peaches.

title: low calorie steak diane
directions: Combine oleo and Worcestershire sauce in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.

Add mushrooms and onions and saute until tender. Place steaks between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using meat mallet or rolling pin. Spreads 1/2 teaspoon mustard on one side of each steak.

title: christmas pecans
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then gradually add brown sugar.
Stir pecans into meringue. Drop spoonfuls of pecan meringue into melted butter in pan. Spoon butter over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool completely, then pack in airtight containers.
Great for gifts or just to nibble.

title: 1 - 2 - 3 - 4 cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in four 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: nose bag snack mix
directions: Into large bowl, measure cereal, sugar, butterscotch pieces and peanuts.
Mix with hands, coarsely crumbling cereal.
Drizzle with butter; toss.
Spoon individual servings into small plastic bags. Makes 24 servings (about 1/4 cup each).

title: shrimp salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to lemon Jell-O and let gel.
Then beat.
Beat together half and half, mayonnaise, pimento cheese and onion.
Then add to gel.
Add shrimp, salt, eggs, celery and green pepper.
Mold.
Serves 11 to 12.

title: pineapple monkey bread
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, preserves, almond and cinnamon until well blended.
Remove from heat and add pineapple.
Spoon half of mixture into greased Bundt pan.
Arrange half of biscuits, standing on edge in pan.
Cover with remaining fruit mixture, and then remaining biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Invert onto wire rack or serving platter to cool completely.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppycock
directions: Melt in saucepan all ingredients except popped corn.
Cook, stirring continually, to hard crack stage (300°).
Pour over popcorn and stir to cover popcorn.

title: sweet carrot bread
directions: *May substitute zucchini for carrots.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook noodles; put into greased casserole. Mix soup, milk and salt; stir well.
Add cheese; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; pour over noodles.
Sprinkle toasted almonds on top.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash and cut bell peppers in half and remove seeds.
Mix raw hamburger meat, onion and cooked rice.
Add 1/2 can of the Hunt's tomato sauce special to the mixture; mix well.
Stuff pepper halves with meat mixture.
Mix remaining 1/2 can of sauce with the tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Pour over peppers and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in top of double boiler.
Slowly add cream, then pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip candy in chocolate mixture and return to wax paper.
Makes 30 pieces of candy.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Drain grease.
Brown ground meat; drain grease. Add remainder of ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef brisket
directions: For every 2 pounds of brisket get additional sauce and soup mix.
Trim excess fat off brisket. Mix chili sauce and onion; mix well.
Spread on both sides of brisket.
Cook with the fat side up.
Wrap in tinfoil (leave space above meat, in other words don't wrap tightly but seal tightly).
Cook at 325° for a minimum of two and a half hours, three hours is better for tender meat.
Let it sit for 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.
Makes its own gravy and is a great easy dish for company.
Serve with rice.

title: frosting
directions: For a quick frosting, mix ingredients together.
Spread on cake while hot.
Place in broiler for a few minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for approximately 80 minutes. Frost when cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put Jell-O, sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Pour in boiling water.
Cook until clear.
Cool; add a box of strawberries, mashed.
Pour into pie shell and serve.
You can use any kind of berries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add beaten egg and vanilla; add flour.
Shape dough into small balls (size of marbles).
Place on cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Press flat with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: bruschetta
directions: Combine garlic and 4 Tbsp. olive oil in a small bowl. Let stand several hours to flavor the oil. Strain oil, saving garlic pieces.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Add other ingredients, then cool.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheesy chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Dip chicken in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Cook in a saucepan in oil.
Mix soup with broccoli.
Press bread crumbs into greased casserole dish and layer chicken, broccoli mixture and cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then raise heat to broil for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Mix popped corn with candy and nuts.
Melt butter, oil and marshmallows in saucepan.
When melted, pour over popcorn mixture.
Press mixture into greased tube pan (angel food cake pan).
Cover with foil to keep moist.
Turn out and decorate as desired.

title: butterscotch striped delight
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, pecans, 3 packs NutraSweet and melted margarine.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 2 tablespoons milk and 4 packs NutraSweet until smooth.
Add 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread over crust.
Mix together instant pudding and 3 1/2 cups milk.
Beat well.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread 1/2 container of Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle pecan chips on top.

title: lemon angel dessert
directions: Cut brown from cake and cut cake into small pieces.
Using a hammer, crush lemon sour balls into powder.
Mix pie filler with 1 1/2 cups of the Cool Whip.
Add some of the lemon sour balls powder.
Now start layering the pieces of cake alternating with pie filler and Cool Whip mixture.
Finish dessert by spreading remaining Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with some of the crushed lemon balls.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Use a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.

title: chicken and noodle squares
directions: Put onion, parsley, salt, pepper and chicken in pot; cover with water.
Cook about 2 hours.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Mix well. Add salt and enough flour to stick together.
Roll out thin; cut in squares.
Dry 2 to 3 hours.
Turn a few times while drying. After chicken is cooked, drop in dried noodles squares.
Cook until tender.

title: quick microwave mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Layer ingredients in a pie pan and heat in microwave until soft enough for dip consistency.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and boil hard for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter. Mix fast.
Drop by spoonful or press in a pan; cool.

title: cherry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Chop 1/2 cup walnuts coarsely for topping.
Set aside.
Chop remaining 1/2 cup finely.

title: freezer peaches
directions: Stir and cool.
Pour over sliced fresh peaches in freezer boxes.

title: diane thibault's macaroni & cheese
directions: Cook Macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
In saucepan, melt Butter; blend in Flour, Salt and Pepper.
Add Milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add Onion if desired and Cheese stir until melted.
Mix Cheese sauce with Macaroni.
Turn into 1-1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350 for 55 - 60 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sinful trifle
directions: Cool cake; cut into squares.
Put half of the cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or punch bowl.
To each box of pudding, add 1 2/3 cups of the milk and 1/3 cup of Amaretto.
Spoon half of the pudding over the cake, half the Cool Whip and 2 Heath bars, chopped. Repeat.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll in walnuts.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Grated carrot may be added also.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Cook macaroni, al dente.
Combine beef, tomatoes, sauce and macaroni; salt and pepper to taste.
Garlic may be added, if desired.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed.
Recipe doubles great and grated Parmesan is fantastic on serving.

title: chicken bean casserole
directions: Blend milk, cream cheese, salt and garlic salt. Add 1/2 of Parmesan cheese. Alternate layers of beans and chicken. Pour mixture over this. Top with rest of Parmesan cheese and Durkee French fried onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients together.
Spread over first layer.
Prepare pudding according to box instructions.
Spread pudding over 2nd layer. Top with a layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: fluffy pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice.
Add gelatine dissolved in 1 cup cold water.
Add salt, pineapple and sugar or sweetener.
Add chopped maraschino cherries.

title: love notes(lemon bars)
directions: Cut flour and powdered sugar into butter until mixture clings together.
Press dough into 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool to room temperature before putting on the topping.
This is essential for a crisp crust.

title: cracker chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Crumble the crackers and place on wax paper. Wash chicken.
Dip the chicken in the butter and then roll it in the crackers (coating both sides).
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (pour extra butter and crackers over chicken) and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix well and shape into 6 patties.
Brown in 1 to 2 tablespoons oil, drain off fat and add balance of mushroom mixture to which you have added 1/2 cup water.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes, covered, until meat is done.
Place patties on serving platter and pour sauce over meat and serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package; drain well.
Melt butter; add stuffing crumbs to butter and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix together jello, cornstarch and sugar.
Add water and mix thoroughly.
Cook over medium high heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil and is transparent. Remove from heat.
Cool and set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy potato chowder
directions: Place potatoes, onion and carrots in a kettle or large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil and cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Add corn, ham, bay leaves, garlic salt, pepper, parsley flakes and butter plus enough milk to make soup desired consistency.
Simmer uncovered over medium to low heat for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Make pudding according to package directions and add 1 teaspoon pineapple extract.
Cool and add pineapple; mix.
Layer banana, coconut and nuts in bottom of pie shell.
Pour pudding mixture over layers, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons coconut and pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Saute zucchini and carrots separately in 1/2 tablespoon oil each until tender-crisp.
Combine eggs and Parmesan.
In 3 bowls, stir 1/3 mixture separately into spinach, carrots and zucchini. Spoon 2/3 cup sauce into 9-inch square baking pan.
Place half of noodles over sauce.
Spread spinach into pan; top with 1/3 of Provolone, carrots, 2/3 cup sauce, another 1/3 of Provolone and zucchini.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce; cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, remove foil and sprinkle with remaining Provolone; bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Defrost bread according to directions; allow to rise.
Spread bread onto floured surface and pat into approximately 16 x 10-inch rectangle.
Will be difficult, can be smaller if unable to spread. Spread thin layer of tomato sauce, leaving 1-inch border without sauce.
Sprinkle with spices.
Press pepperoni between paper towels to remove excess oil.
Layer lots of pepperoni on sauce, sprinkle with cheese.
Fold 1/3 of bread over middle 1/3, then 1/3 over that, using small amount of water on fingertips, seal edges.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture along with buttermilk. Stir in fruits, dates and nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: breakfast soup
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: yummy baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese, if desired.

title: poached fish
directions: Heat 1 1/2-inches of water, onion, lemon, parsley, bay leaf, salt and peppercorns to boiling in a 10-inch skillet.
Reduce heat.
Arrange fish in single layer in skillet.
Simmer, uncovered, until fish fillets flake easily with fork, 4 to 6 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy; add egg, beating well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Spoon 1 heaping tablespoon of this mixture into center of each cupcake.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool before storing in the refrigerator.

title: old fashioned chewy molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, ginger, salt and soda together and set aside.
Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add egg, molasses, vanilla and milk and combine thoroughly with creamed ingredients. Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in oatmeal until all ingredients are well blended.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into casserole dish.
Alternate potatoes with onion flakes and salt as you slice potatoes into dish.
Brown sausage and place on top of potatoes.
Make gravy from sausage grease.
Pour over top of potato mixture.
Bake, covered, until potatoes are done in 350° oven or microwave on High.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine cheese and tomatoes and heat until all cheese is melted.
Add meat and stir well.
Great idea for preparing in crock-pot.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: In a pot, combine all ingredients, except pecans and vanilla. Cook mixture over low heat until it forms soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Beat well until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in vanilla and pecans, using a teaspoon to form individual pralines on wax paper.
Let stand to cool.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: florida hash
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in shortening.
When onion and pepper are tender, add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Simmer with lid off until juice is cooked down as much as you desire. Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together the 4 well-beaten eggs, parsley flakes and the three cheeses.
Set aside.
Fry the ground chuck and drain.
Mix into the fried ground chuck the salt, pepper, spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Cook the noodles according to the package directions and drain.
In a 9x12 inch pan layer the noodles, meat with sauce and the cheese mixture, ending with cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place
cheeses
in small mixing bowl, let stand at room temperature
until
soft.
Beat
in
onion
and Worcestershire sauce on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy.
Cover and refrigerate at
least 8 hours.
Shape into 1 large ball or 36 1-inch balls.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, pecans, graham cracker crumbs, egg whites and chocolate chips together.
Put in pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Place in a large saucepan the first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for exactly 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix in the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop onto waxed paper by rounded teaspoonfuls and allow to cool.

title: fruit salad recipe
directions: Put pudding mix, poppy seed and juice from can of fruit in container; shake vigorously for 30 seconds.
Pour mixture over fruits.
Let sit in refrigerator several hours.
You can add fruits of your choice and nuts to this mixture.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine water, oats and margarine.
Cover, let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugar and eggs; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Bake in oblong pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray large pizza pan with nonstick spray.
Place crescent rolls flat in pan and pat out to form pie shell by sealing edges together and rolling up dough around the rim of the pan.
Top crust with drained sausage, crumbled hash browns, grated cheese and beaten eggs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are set and crust is golden brown.
Slice with pizza cutter and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili con carne
directions: This recipe has been used for Bethel Chili Supper.
It serves 25 people.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg.
Mix vegetables and mushroom soup; half cook them.
Mix with ground beef.
Put in casserole dish.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey lime grilled chicken
directions: In a resealable plastic bag, combine the honey, soy, and lime juice, mix well.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Seal and refrigerate for 30 - 45 minutes.
Drain and discard the marinade. Grill the chicken uncovered, over medium heat for 6 - 7 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix mayonnaise, egg, parsley, mustard, salt and pepper, pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add crab meat and 1 cup bread crumbs; mix well.
Shape in 8 patties and coat with remaining 1 cup crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: ginger salmon cakes
directions: Squeeze 1 1/2 tablespoons juice from lemon.
In small jar, shake together lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon ginger, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper until salt dissolves.
Add 3 tablespoons oil and shake to combine.

title: berry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; pour into 2 goblets. Freeze 15 minutes for cool, lite treat.

title: soda cracker pie or macaroon pie
directions: Roll crackers until very
fine.
Beat
egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar gradually
and beat until mixture stands in soft peaks.
Fold in
vanilla,
cracker
crumbs, baking powder and walnuts.
Spread evenly
in
well-greased 9-inch pie plate and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serves six to eight.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Mix taco seasoning according to package directions in the hamburger.
Add refried beans to this. Spread this mixture in a jelly roll pan.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot at 325°.
Scoop with tortilla chips.

title: orange cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Blend white cake mix, 4 egg whites and oil.
Mix jello mixture into cake batter.
Grease and flour cake pan (9 x 12-inch).
Pour batter in cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Make holes in cake with a fork all the way to the bottom.
Mix orange juice and powdered sugar and pour over cake.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix baking soda with flour.
Combine rest of ingredients.

title: zesty vegetable enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until warm. Spray a 2-quart rectangular baking dish (with Pam).

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange sherbet and mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate until set.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream oleo, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add yolks.
Mix soda with buttermilk. Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Add pecans and coconut to batter and fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 x 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill overnight.

title: dip for apples and strawberries
directions: Mix together and serve as dip for fruit.

title: relish
directions: Grind all vegetables (coarse blade).
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand for 8 to 12 hours.
Rinse and drain.
Squeeze excess water.
Combine sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients in blender until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Coat well with flour; fry chicken until brown in hot oil.
Then remove from skillet.
Add vegetables and cook until wilted.
Put chicken back in skillet and cover.
Cook slowly until tender (about 30 minutes).
Add rice to chicken.
Stir thoroughly for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour beer over mixture and stir.
Add salt and cook slowly (about 30 minutes) until rice is cooked.

title: chile rellenos casserole i
directions: Wash chiles and pat dry.
In a pie plate, layer half the chiles and 1/3 of the grated cheese.
Repeat layers, leaving 1/3 of the cheese for topping.
Beat eggs.
Add flour and milk.
Beat until blended.
Pour the mixture over the chiles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread tomato sauce evenly over the top; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: rocky road peanut butter squares
directions: Heat syrup and sugar to boiling in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Immediately remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Place cereal in a large bowl. Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal, stirring until well coated.
Cool slightly about 2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows. Press mixture in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, using buttered back of a spoon.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Heat chocolate and shortening over low heat until melted.
Drizzle over squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and chop into small pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, eggs, mushroom soup, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix together broccoli and soup mixture and put into a greased casserole dish.
Crush 1 stack of Ritz Crackers and saute in 1 stick of melted oleo. Spread on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter very slowly until soft, 1/2 to 1 hour. Add flour and continue cooking very slowly for 15 minutes.
Do not brown!
Stir in broth and bouillon.
Slowly add water, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for 1 to 2 hours partly covered.
Adjust seasonings.
Serves 30.

title: chicken de normandy
directions: Mix stuffing, butter and broth.
Put half of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients together, except cheese and place on stuffing.
Then, place remaining stuffing on top and cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
May want to wait until last 10 minutes to put cheese on top.
You can make ahead and put in refrigerator.
Let sit out 1 hour before baking.

title: sausage and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix browned sausage with oregano, salt and cheese.
Spread bread slices on cookie sheets and spread with mixture.
Place under broiler until bread is toasted and cheese is bubbly.
These may be made ahead of time and frozen.
Serve hot.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Combine sugar, cream and dates, stirring constantly. Cook to the soft ball stage, 236°.
Add butter and allow to cool until lukewarm. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir (smooth) until creamy. Pour on a damp towel and mold into a roll about 2-inches.
When cold, remove towel. Roll in powdered sugar.
Slice with a sharp knife.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Combine the buttermilk, liquid shortening and dissolved yeast; mix.
Add
to this the remaining ingredients.
Stir and mix well. Pour
out
onto
floured board; sprinkle flour over the top of dough
as
you make biscuits.
Place well apart on greased cookie sheet.
Let
rise
to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot-cabbage casserole
directions: Toss cabbage, onion and carrots.
Combine celery seed, soup, sour cream and horseradish.
Fold soup mixture into vegetables. Spoon mixture into a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine stuffing and oleo, sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix until crumbly.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, eggs, lemon extract and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos; set aside.
Blend butter, cream cheese and sugar. Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Add to butter mixture.
In a large flowerpot, layer Oreo crumbs and pudding.
Bottom and top layers are crumbs.
Chill.
Stick flower bouquet in pot.
Serve with trowel.

title: caribbean spice chicken(serves 4)
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a large measuring cup. Combine spices in a small bowl.
Stir 1/4 teaspoon spice mixture, along with cornstarch, into pineapple juice.
Set aside.

title: brisket of beef
directions: Slice onion and place in the bottom of roaster pan.
Put brisket on top and sprinkle with garlic powder and lemon pepper. Cook at 450° for 30 minutes uncovered.
Pour Pepsi over; cover with foil and cook at 350° for 3 hours.
This can be cooked the day before, then sliced thinly and reheated with barbecue sauce over the top.
Delish.

title: frosting cake
directions: Mix all together, then pour in greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Mix everything together except chips in a 5-quart baking dish.
Crush chips and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cook at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: potato deutscher(casserole)
directions: Grate raw potatoes on a coarse grater.
Soak cubes in 1 cup milk.
Add beaten eggs to soaked bread and then add potatoes.
Add the remainder of the milk and seasoning.
Place in a greased baking dish and pour sour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.
Serves 6.
Sour cream on top tastes like cheese after baking.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together the bran, flour, raisins, soda, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
Blend milk, honey, oil and egg. Add these to dry ingredients. Stir just until moistened. Spoon into greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until muffins pull away from sides of pan.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in saucepan.
Add boiling water; cook, stirring, until clear.
Let stand until completely cool; cover so a scum will not form.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Add vanilla. Gradually beat in cornstarch mixture on slow speed; turn back on high and beat well.
Spread over cooled filling.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or pleasingly browned.

title: no weep meringue
directions: As the seasons change, you can change the ingredients to fit what is available to you and make this fruit-streusel coffee cake a year round and holiday favorite.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of oblong dish.
Mix 2 soups and 1 cup broth in a bowl and heat in microwave.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Mix butter, 1 cup broth, bag of Pepperidge dressing mix. Mix well and spoon on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued pork tenderloin(outdoor cooking)
directions: Trim and discard excess fat from pork.
In a deep bowl, stir to mix garlic, ginger, chilies, mustard, brown sugar, orange peel, oil, vinegar and soy sauce.
Roll pork in mixture, then cover and chill at least 30 minutes or up to 3 hours; turn meat several times.
Lift meat from marinade; drain briefly and place above a solid bed of very hot coals.
Brush with marinade; cover grill and open dampers.
Cook, turning to brown evenly, and baste occasionally with marinade.
Cook about 20 minutes only.
Meat thermometer inserted will register 150° to 155°.
Add water to marinade to make 1/2 cup total.
Add cornstarch and stir over high heat.
To serve, cut meat into thin slices and spoon over sauce. Makes 3 servings.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then in flavored bread crumbs.
Fry slowly in olive oil in which you have lightly browned 1 clove of garlic (remove).
Put all in Dutch oven.
Cover with 1 cup Marsala wine, to which is added 1 tablespoon parsley flakes.
If not enough liquid, add hot water.
Simmer all for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, or until meat is tender.

title: chocolate filled snow drops
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add sifted flour and nuts; blend well.
Chill dough.

title: banana muffins
directions: Add dry ingredients to oil, egg, milk and banana.
Mix.
Line muffin tins or grease pans.
Fill tins 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese until soft.
Add onion; mix well. Rinse and drain shrimp well; add to cheese mixture.
Salt to taste.
Form into ball; cover with shrimp sauce.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Gradually stir milk into soup in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) for 10 minutes; stir.
Cover and microwave until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes longer; stir.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: mad hatter's breakfast
directions: In mixing bowl, beat egg; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
You can use a blender instead.
Pour into glass and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 1 cup.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Put apples and cranberries through a food chopper.
Add 1 cup water to box of Jell-O.
Dissolve.
Add all other ingredients. Pour all into serving bowl and refrigerate.

title: cauliflower or broccoli soup
directions: Cut cauliflower or broccoli into small pieces and cook for 45 minutes with onion in chicken broth.
Make a white sauce on stove with oleo, flour and milk; cook until thickened.
Add to cauliflower or broccoli and bring to a boil.
Add half and half and bring to a boil.
Ready to eat!

title: barley casserole
directions: Heat butter in frypan.
Add barley and saute until light brown; place in heavy casserole.
Heat 1/2 remaining butter in saucepan and saute onions until soft, but not brown.
Saute mushrooms in remaining butter.
Add to other ingredients.
Stir in hot consomme, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat 35 to 40 minutes until barley absorbs the consomme.
Serves 6.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in freezer.
Fill freezer to the line with milk.
If fruit is used, add an additional cup of sugar.

title: philly cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cheese, cream cheese and margarine.
Mix until well blended.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Mold into ball.
Makes 2 cheese balls.
Great Christmas gifts.
Can be rolled in mixture of 3/4 cup chopped pecans and 1/4 cup pistachio nuts.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown meat in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, 2 cups of water, salt and pepper. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: fondue
directions: Coat cheese with flour.
Pour wine in pot.
When bubbles rise, add lemon juice.
Add cheese by handfuls until cheese melts.
Add brandy and spices until blended.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour mixture over baked crust and return to oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool a few minutes, then sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.
Let cool before cutting into desired size bars or squares.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain; add salt, pepper and jalapenos.
Combine corn, Accent and onion in corn can.
Mix 1 cup corn and eggs into cornbread mix until moistened.
Pour 1/2 cornbread mix into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle on meat, then cheese, then remaining corn.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or golden brown.

title: ritz cracker treats
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until thick.
Cool slightly. Spread on Ritz crackers.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with about 1 tablespoon of the melted margarine.
Beat egg and water in a shallow dish.
Mix flour and salt in another shallow dish.
Dip about 1/4 of the vegetables into egg mixture.
Remove 1 piece at a time; roll in flour mixture to coat.
Place in pan.
Repeat with remaining vegetables.
Pour remaining margarine carefully over each vegetable piece and into pan.
Bake uncovered, turning once, until vegetables are crisp-tender and coating is golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: italian soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add all the other ingredients and one can(soup) of water.
Simmer for about one hour.

title: chicken rose
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Let marinate a few hours or overnight.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Cream butter until it resembles whipped cream.
Add sugar slowly, beating well.
Add flour gradually, blending thoroughly. Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill several hours.
Knead dough slightly on lightly floured board; form into a smooth ball.
Roll to about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for approximately 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand about 3 minutes before removing cookies to cooler rack.
When cold, decorate cookies as desired with butter icing, cake decorations or candied fruits.

title: cottage cheese cookies
directions: Combine butter, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Add cottage cheese, then the dry ingredients.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet (greased); flatten.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, salt, vanilla, oats, coconut and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery in large skillet. Mix together the remaining ingredients. Add to hamburger mixture. Simmer one hour on medium heat or until liquid is absorbed. Keep a lid on the pan while simmering.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix until blended.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Fill with batter and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in a bowl until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping, spread on bottom of crust.
Pour milk into a bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Mix until thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients; knead 5 minutes.
Let rise at 85° for 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Fry in deep fat at 375°. Drain.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare and thinly slice potatoes.
Toss slices in 1 cup cold water and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Drain.

title: (easy) creamy crock-pot chicken and mushrooms
directions: You will need a large crock-pot.

title: zucchini with stuffing
directions: Saute vegetables in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients, reserving 3/4 cup croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with reserved croutons tossed with remaining melted margarine.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking 10 minutes.

title: hash brown potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a large skillet with water and salad dressing.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and potatoes are tender (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Add more water if necessary during cooking to keep from sticking.
Chill.
Mix potatoes, onions, celery, green pepper and chopped eggs together.
In separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, mustard and seasoned salt.
Pour over potatoes mixture and toss gently to mix. Place in serving bowl.
Makes 8 servings.
Boy does it taste good.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and cinnamon.
Mix 1/4 cup of flour mixture with nuts and gumdrops.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar and water and beat again.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and gumdrops.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: new mexican corn custard
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in order listed.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 30 minutes more or reduce to 150° and leave for several hours until ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in saucepan.
Heat until marshmallows are melted; let cool.
Add whipped cream and fruit cocktail; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ever so easy fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Grease a 9-inch tube pan (line with foil) or use generously greased and floured 10-inch fluted pan. Sift together flour and baking soda, then set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. Blend in dry ingredients. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 50 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Set popcorn aside.
Add peanuts to popcorn in bag before adding caramel mixture.
Place sugar, margarine, corn syrup, salt and vanilla in adequate bowl in microwave until margarine is melted. Stir.
Put back in for 2 minutes on High.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon soda (will puff).
Pour hot mixture over popcorn in bag and shake.
Put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and shake.
Repeat one more time.
Back final time for 1/2 minute on High.
Remove and shake.
Spread on waxed paper to dry.

title: sour milk corn bread
directions: Combine egg, melted shortening and sour milk.
Stir in water containing dissolved soda.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat smooth. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve cake squares topped with sour cream or whipped cream and a dab of applesauce.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange in baking dish.
One top of each chop, place an apple slice, an onion slice and a teaspoon of brown sugar.
Stir water, vinegar and raisins into skillet with pork chop drippings.
Bring to a boil; pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable beef soup(makes as much as you need)
directions: If you agree on ingredients, you may add: fresh mushrooms, red or green peppers or other vegetables that are available.
If there are enough fresh veggies around, you can eliminate the frozen or canned ones, but the cooking times have to be thought about.

title: tot's rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco and 1/2 cup of sugar while you soak 2 packages of yeast in one cup of warm water.
Measure out 6 cups of flour (before sifting).

Add 2 teaspoons of salt and sift 3 times. Add 1 cup boiling water to the Crisco and sugar and let it cool. Once it is cool, add the yeast; beat in 2 eggs and add flour. (Tot says that the secret for making light bread is to add the flour gradually and beat with a fork after each addition.)
Let rise until double.
Stir down and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, pat them out in your hand (flour hands first), making an oval.
Put a bit of melted butter in center and fold over.
Let them rise until double (about 2 hours) before baking in a 425° oven.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pickling pig cake
directions: Mix together and bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour batter into melted butter. Pour peaches with juice into batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all together well and put in a well greased 13x9x1 1/2 inch dish and bake in slow oven until brown - time varies according to your oven.
Good hot or cold.
Cut in 1 1/2 inch squares.
Yields: 12-15 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Then combine both mixtures.
Rolls out better if chilled.
Makes 3 crusts or makes 2 crusts with lattice top and 1 crust alone.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Stir until berries separate and gelatin begins to thicken.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no-cal zucchini
directions: Place all the ingredients in a medium covered saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; cook for 10 minutes longer.
Watch carefully to be sure liquid has not evaporated.
Add liquid if necessary, 1 tablespoon at a time. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix with sour cream and soups.
Mix in hash browns.
Season with salt and pepper. Can sprinkle sesame seed and paprika on top. Bake at 300° for 2 hours in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: onion bread
directions: Split loaf of French bread the long way.
Mix ingredients together and spread on bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
