Good served with spaghetti or lasagna.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together and spread on pizza crust.
Mix vegetables together and spread evenly on top of cream cheese mixture.
Press lightly.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix together turkey, gravy and salt.
Turn into 7 3/4 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Beat together potatoes, onion and 1 egg. Spread over turkey mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package, then combine all other ingredients in punch bowl.

title: bob hall's jamestown parmesan mustard dressing(good for cole slaw)
directions: Mix, shake and allow to sit overnight.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Peel carrots, boil or microwave until tender.
Mash until chunky (use hand masher).
Add flour, baking powder, beaten eggs and pinch of cinnamon.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Combine with carrots and stir together.
Place in buttered Pyrex dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. Lower oven to 350° and bake for another 45 minutes.

title: deluxe pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan as directed on box.
Mix pineapple with sugar; bring to boil.
Pour over cake.
Cook vanilla pudding according to directions on box; pour over cake and let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on cake; top with frozen coconut.
You can add crushed nuts, if desired.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Reserve 1 cup cookie crumbs for topping (I use nuts instead). Mix remaining crumbs with butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer ice cream, fudge topping, pecans and whipped topping over crumbs.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs or nuts.
Freeze until serving time.

title: aggie's cookies
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the softened butter or margarine.
Beat or squeeze ingredients together.
Roll dough between hands into small balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Rub butter on the bottom of a glass and dip it in granulated sugar.
Flatten balls of dough with glass bottom.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in mustard and cheese; heat over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: nacho snack mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine margarine and seasonings in cup and pour over dry mixture; toss to coat. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool and store in airtight container.

title: poached salmon steaks
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large frypan with cover.
Add parsley, carrot, onion and celery.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add peppercorns, clove, bay leaf, salt and wine.
Bring to a boil. Place the salmon steaks in the pan and allow to simmer (just below boiling), covered.
After 5 to 7 minutes, gently turn over and continue to cook for another 7 to 10 minutes.
The salmon is done when it flakes.
You will notice a color change, too, from bright pink to lighter pink.
Serve with mayonnaise or lemon on the side and the remaining bottle of wine.
(I like a Johannisberg Riesling.)

title: cracker salad (mock)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add more mayonnaise if mixture is too dry. Refrigerate. Serve with any kind of meat.

title: orange salad
directions: This salad can be used with cherry Jell-O and add nuts for a Christmas salad.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Soften Knox gelatine in cold water.
Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Add Knox mixture, sugar, horseradish, salt and vinegar or lemon juice.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add celery, beets, carrot, cabbage and minced onion.
Mold as desired and serve with mayonnaise.
Fresh and pretty.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; cool.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add to jello.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups or use nonstick muffin pans.
Make buttermilk by mixing the milk and vinegar.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine the bran cereal, hot water, honey, oil, salt and egg.
Let stand for 1 or 2 minutes.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding eggs one at a time.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour or more at 325°.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown meat in oil slightly. Add garlic, salt, onion, green pepper and chili powder; saute 5 minutes. Mix in remaining ingredients, except olives and cheese; pour into a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle olives and cheese on top; bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Serves 8.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam or grease with shortening (9 x 13-inch). Pour in pineapple.
Add blueberries, mixed with 3/4 cup sugar. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of berries.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional) and 1/4 cup sugar. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Add creamed butter to cornbread mix. Add eggs. Mix broccoli, onions and cheese; fold into cornbread mix.
Blend all together, fold in sour cream last.
Pour into a greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick after 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add eggs, oil, pecans and strawberries.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into loaf pan (well-greased).
Fill pans a little more than 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in casserole; cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup; cook on high at 300° or until hard crack stage.
Take off heat and add coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto marble slab and foil.
Cool lightly and cut with sharp knife to make pieces.
Cool to warm.
Break into pieces and coat with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies(servings:  24)
directions: Beat together butter, peanut butter, honey, salt, vanilla and egg.
Add flour and baking soda; mix evenly.
Fold in peanuts and chips.
Chill until firm.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheets.
Press with fork until slightly flat.
Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: sourdough bread for bread machine
directions: Mix and set out overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: barbara's hamburger supper
directions: Pat out hamburger patties.
Cook until done.
Drain out all grease.
Take patties out of skillet.
Add cream of celery soup and enough water to make gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add patties back to skillet.
Simmer.

title: raspberry walnut chicken salad(serves 6)
directions: Mix chicken, celery and walnuts together.
Add salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, mix mayo and vinaigrette well.
Add mayo mixture to chicken and blend.
Serve on crusty French bread or on a bed of lettuce.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat sour cream and oil.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well. Add vanilla, pudding and cake mix.
Bake 5 minutes, no less.
Add chips.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crappie batter
directions: Blend oil and water and add remaining ingredients.
Dip fillets in batter and deep fry at 375° to 400° or until golden brown.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add bouillon cube to boiling water.
Remove pan from heat; add cold milk slowly, stirring to keep paste smooth, then add bouillon water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add shrimp, lemon juice and just heat.
Serve with rice and curry accompaniments.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Salt, pepper and brown; set aside. Remove excess fat.
Brown celery and onion in skillet where chicken was browned.
Add rice to celery and onion for about 5 minutes, stir.
Place rice in casserole.
Add chicken pieces on top.
In skillet, heat 4 cups water and 2 chicken bouillon cubes.
Add to casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until water is absorbed and rice tender, or microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cool and chocolate
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Put into a cold cut keeper.
Mix the pudding as directed on the box.
Pour over cake. Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes to chill.
Pour Cool Whip over the pudding and cake.
Grate Hershey bars over top.
Seal and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 18 servings.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Mix and cook at 350° for 40
minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, egg, remaining parsley and salt.
In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, spoon 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Layer with noodles.
Spread with 1/2 Ricotta mixture.
Top with 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layering.
Cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake 25 minutes longer.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken up into desired pieces, trimming fat. Place chicken in 9 x 13 pan and season with salt and pepper. Combine soups, water and rice. Mix well and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until chicken is done.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins just until blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes and turn out on wire rack.
Gooood.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into an unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double layer chocolate pie
directions: Mix cream cheese 1 Tbsp. milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flavoring until smooth.
Blend in chocolate (melted) one at a time.
On high, beat in eggs, one at a time, for 2 to 3 minutes each egg.
Fold in 2 cups of the prepared whip topping and pour mixture into pie shell.
Top with remaining topping and chill for 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with shaved chocolate curls if desired.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light
and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine
flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add to creamed
mixture
alternately with sour cream beginning and ending with
flour
mixture.
Stir
in coconut and flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in
center
comes
out
clean.
Cool
in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan;
cool completely.

title: english muffins(no knead)
directions: Combine half flour, yeast, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
In a small pan, heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add liquid to dry mix and beat well.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle pan with corn meal.
Place batter in pan and sprinkle top lightly with corn meal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about an hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until done and lightly brown.
Remove from pan and cool on a rack.

title: butterscotch balls
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar and peanut butter, like you would dough.
Form small balls and refrigerate 5 to 10 minutes. Melt paraffin and tidbits in top of double boiler.
After this has melted, dip ball with toothpick and put on wax paper.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add one egg
at
a
time;
beat well, then add flour and milk. Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix everything and serve on top of meat, eggs, beans, etc. Optional:
You may add chopped cilantro or chopped avocado.

title: dub rhodes chili(texas state champion, 1960's)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Add Coke and mustard.
Heat to boil, then turn down to just a blubber now and then.
Second hour, add salt pork.
Third hour, add garlic.
Fourth hour, add oregano and chili pequins.
Fifth hour, add tomatoes, liquid and pulp.
Simmer until 10% of liquid is gone and beans break up.
When adding water, always add warm water.
Keep water 1/4-inch above beans until 5th hour.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Stir together cake mix, eggs and butter in bowl (mixture will be stiff).
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: macaroni and cheese with vegetables
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Drain green beans and mixed vegetables.
Add to macaroni and cheese.
Stir well. Goes well with any meat.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch baking pans.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently (or 300 strokes by hand).
Batter will be very thick.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream (or other icing, Cream Cheese Icing).

title: curried popcorn
directions: Combine nuts, curry powder and garlic salt.
Bake on jelly roll pan in 350° oven for 10 minutes, stirring often, until browned.
Immediately toss with popcorn.

title: gourmet meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, water, cream cheese and oil. Shape into 20 balls.
Heat skillet to 340° with oil.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides.
Cover and reduce heat to 280°; cook for 15 minutes.
Remove meatballs from pan and reduce to simmer.
Spoon off drippings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add powdered sugar, melted butter and chocolate syrup.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Add marshmallows and nut meats.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour in mixture.
Top with more crumbs; chill overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in a large bowl.
Pour into crust.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually add water.
Over medium heat stir constantly until boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: poor county oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla. Mix.
Sift flour, spices, soda and salt.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool a few minutes and place on rack.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Cream together first three ingredients. Add crumbs and pineapple.
Bake at 350° until brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco party wings
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, then add salad dressing. Stir until blended.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix with hands.
Will be crumbly.
Barely flour board.
Roll out 1/4-inch.
Cut into strips with pastry wheel.
Bake about 10 minutes in 400°
oven until beginning to brown.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large bowl, place butter and peanut butter.
Microwave on High until butter melts (1 1/2 to 2 minutes).
Stir until blended. Add remaining ingredients; stir until lumps of sugar disappear. Microwave on High until softened but not bubbly (1 to 1 1/2 minutes).
Stir.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking pan. Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store refrigerated.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour hot water over oats and let stand.
Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Sift cake flour with soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture and then add oats.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: broccoli and zucchini pasta
directions: Steam broccoli in a small amount of water or in a steamer basket until crisp-tender, about 7 minutes.
In the meantime, cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cherries and walnuts. Mix well.
Cut cherries and walnuts into small pieces and mix with batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Combine crabmeat, cracker crumbs and eggs. Add onion, bell pepper, celery, mayonnaise, butter, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, dry mustard and salt and pepper. Mix all together well. May be cooked in quiche dish or in devil crab shells. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over hot water. Remove from heat.
Add milk, vanilla and peanuts.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a buttered cookie sheet or onto waxed paper. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In buttered baking pan, place chicken.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at
325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple jello
directions: Chill evaporated milk until very cold, then whip.
Heat pineapple to boil; add jello and 1 cup water.
Cool until partially set; whip jello.
Then fold whipped milk to jello and chill.
Add nuts last.

title: batter fried shrimp
directions: Combine 1/2 cup vegetable oil and egg, beating well.
Add the next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Dip shrimp into batter; fry in 1 inch vegetable oil, medium hot.
Cook about 30 seconds on each side, or until lightly browned.
Do not overcook.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: jupes salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes a large bowl.

title: fried rats
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: quantity pancake mix
directions: Mix well and store in tight container.

title: tater tot surprise
directions: Brown Tater Tots.
Set aside in bowl the soup, milk and cheese.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the Tater Tots, hamburger, broccoli and pour bowl ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham asparagus quiche
directions: Sprinkle
ham
evenly	in
baked
pie	shell.	Arrange asparagus over ham;
sprinkle
Swiss
cheese
over	all.
Beat eggs; add half and half,
salt and pepper until mixed; but not frothy.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture is set.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; saute onion, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Put spaghetti in casserole dish; add broth until moist.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add drained English peas, Ro-Tel and sauteed vegetables.
Add cheese in small chunks.
Warm in oven; stir occasionally until cheese is well blended.

title: white castle hamburger(clone)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; fry in hot skillet.
Serve on buns (cut in thirds).
Garnish with condiments.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Wash, but do not peel the mushrooms.
Chop fine and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes with 1 tablespoon of the butter, the onion and celery seed.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in the boiling water; add to mushrooms and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, melt remaining butter in the top of a double boiler over direct heat.
Add the flour; stir until smooth.
Then add the milk, salt and pepper.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add the mushroom mixture and heat through.
Serves 6.

title: bread turkey stuffing
directions: Saute onion, oil and celery.
Add salt, pepper and sage while breaking up bread in big bowl.
Let sauteed ingredients cool. Pour sauteed ingredients onto bread; mix thoroughly.
Add water. Clean turkey, stuff, tie off and cook as directed.
Makes 3 quarts in a 12-pound turkey.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Add milk, but do not stir.
Sift flour and sugar together and add to milk and butter. Stir.
Drop peaches into filling.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together and pour in pastry shell and bake at 350° until firm.

title: georgia pecan sticks
directions: Cream butter well.
Stir in vanilla, pecans, sugar and flour. Knead well.
Mold dough into pencil size pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1/2-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: rice and cheese casserole
directions: Alternate layers of rice, puree and cheese in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 3/4 of an hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Take off burner.
Add vanilla flavoring and put in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onion until well done.
Drain off grease. Combine remaining ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil and then simmer, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips, grated cheese, crackers and/or cornbread.

title: date balls
directions: Combine dates, egg, sugar and oleo in saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 8 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: zucchini crispies
directions: Place zucchini slices on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, mustard, marjoram and dried thyme; stir well.
Spread 1/2 teaspoon mayonnaise mixture over each zucchini slice.
Combine breadcrumbs, paprika and melted oleo; stir well.
Sprinkle evenly over zucchini slices.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes or until breadcrumbs are browned.
Serve warm.
(Contains 0.9 grams fat and 0 cholesterol.)
Yield:
24 servings.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo until tender.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, cheese and soup to sauteed vegetables.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add chicken and mushrooms.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth.
Drain and add to other ingredients.
Mix well and pour in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: hearty soup
directions: Lightly saute sausage, garlic, onion and bell pepper in the oil. Stir in the cabbage and simmer until it begins to wilt. Stir in the seasonings. Add the chicken stock, vinegar and potatoes. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender. Quickly stir in the flour mixture and sour cream. Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and squash casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in large steamer.
Steam 5 to 8 minutes, until crisp.
Remove and add squash.
Steam.
Combine squash, onion and butter in large bowl.
Mash or not.
Stir in broccoli, eggs, mayonnaise, shredded Cheddar cheese and pepper.
Spoon into 2 lightly greased 2-quart baking dishes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Can use crushed crackers and melted butter for topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Cream again.
Add flour.
Add nuts. Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°. While hot, roll in xxxx sugar.

title: sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in sherbet.
Mix well. Refrigerate until thick, but not firm.
Fold in fruit and whipped cream.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: fajita marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over meat and let marinate for at least 24 hours (fewer for chicken).
Cook on barbecue grill for best results or broil in oven for approximately 5 minutes on each side or according to preferred doneness.
Five minutes is medium-well.

title: sausage kraut bake
directions: Pare and cook potatoes.
Meanwhile, combine sauerkraut and onion; place in casserole dish.
Brown sausage; drain.
Spoon over sauerkraut.
Mash potatoes with milk, butter, salt and pepper. Spread over sausage; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish lined with aluminum foil, place the Minute rice.
Combine cream of chicken mushroom soup and soup can of milk in small mixing bowl.
Pour 1/2 of soup and milk mixture over the rice.
Stir until rice is coated.
Pour dry onion mushroom soup over rice mixture.
Stir until blended.
May also stir in 1/2 of optional mushroom pieces.
Place salt and peppered chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Pour remaining soup and milk mixture over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle remaining dry onion mushroom soup over chicken.
Place remaining optional mushrooms on chicken pieces.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove aluminum foil and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash until nearly tender; drain.
Add oleo, 1/2 bread crumbs, all seasonings and 1/2 cheese.
Pour in beaten eggs. Blend and pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with rest of bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy summer salad
directions: In medium sized mixing bowl, combine the powdered lime Jell-O, drained, crushed pineapple and cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: mary green's chewy lemon cookies
directions: Chill dough long enough to make handling easier (skip if in a hurry).
Dip by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: frittata(easter pie)
directions: Lightly beat eggs in a bowl.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Prepare a large iron skillet by spraying with Pam or wiping with olive oil.
Heat pan and fill pan with the egg mixture.
Cook slowly over moderate heat until bottom half of pie congeals. Remove pan to broiler to cook top half.
When light brown, remove pie to serving dish and cut into wedges as a pie.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: chipped beef cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except for nuts. Bake at 250° for 10 to 15 minutes or microwave. Top with chopped nuts.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in pan.
Put 1 slice of Swiss cheese on top of each.
Spread soup on top of cheese.
Sprinkle crumbs all over.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put ingredients in Dutch oven.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Take off heat, stir in nuts.
Pour in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: hot 'n hearty potato salad
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook onions in margarine 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add potatoes and continue cooking, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes or until heated through (do not boil).
Garnish with parsley and bacon. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken roll ups
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line casserole dish with dried beef. Wrap each breast with strip of bacon.
Put over top of dried beef. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Butter loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Combine sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234° on candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Cool mixture to 120° without stirring.
Bottom of pan will be lukewarm.
Add vanilla; beat vigorously and continuously for 5 to 10 minutes, with a wooden spoon, until candy is thick and no longer glossy.
Mixture will hold its shape when dropped from spoon.
Quickly stir in nuts. Spread evenly in buttered pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: green noodles with ricotta
directions: To make sauce, combine butter with Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and salt and pepper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, butter, salt and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add corn and blend well.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 10 inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes, until set.

title: christmas plum pudding
directions: Combine apple, butter, molasses, eggs and milk.
Sift flour and mix with fruit and nuts.
Combine remaining flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices.
Sift again.
Add to molasses mixture.
Add fruit.
Turn into well-greased molds, filling them 2/3 full.
Cover tightly.
Steam 3 hours.
Serve hot with hard sauce.
Serves 12.

title: saucepan cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter into hot mixture.
Remove from heat and add cornflakes. Drop from a teaspoon onto aluminum foil.
Let cool.

title: potato puff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
One hour before the meal, put in oven with meat.
Will puff up and brown.
Can be made in the morning and refrigerated until ready to use.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together and bake in greased and floured jelly roll
pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost while still warm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients.
Mix enough milk in to make its consistency soft.
Put sliced Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clams gourmet
directions: Combine cheese, clams, parsley, chives, garlic and peppers. Mix until well blended.
Spread mixture on slices of bread.
Place on broiler or cookie sheet.
Broil until golden brown and bubbly, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 25 to 30 slices. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
5 to 10 minutes.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and press into a 10-inch pan, forming a pie crust (be sure to press hamburg mixture up the sides a little).
Mix together the remaining ingredients and put in center of hamburg mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients together.
Parboil cabbage and separate leaves.
Cut out thick part of leaf.
Form oblong meat balls and roll up in cabbage leaves.
Put layer of sauerkraut in bottom of roaster.
Add cabbage rolls and cover with remaining sauerkraut.
Pour tomato juice over top.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: chicken and broccoli braid
directions: Arrange crescent rolls on stone or pan. Combine all ingredients except the egg whites and mix well. Take mixture and place on crescent rolls. Wrap rolls around the filling, pinch and tuck. Brush on egg white. Bake 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch square pan. Cream until light and fluffy the butter.
Beat in gradually the sugar.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add bananas and vanilla or lemon extract.
Sift together flour, baking soda (1 teaspoon sour milk or cream is used) and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with milk or cream.
Spoon into pan.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream on top.

title: rice and monterey jack cheese
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer rice, cheese and sour cream with green chile peppers.
Repeat, ending with sour cream (layers will be thin).
Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Bake 20 to 23 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Do not bake longer.
Serves 12.

title: dump cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend with hands or large spoon.
Drop onto sheets, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light gold.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter. Pat 2 cups of mix into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Reserve rest for topping.

title: cheese rice bake
directions: Into hot, cooked rice, stir 1 cup of the cheese, butter and chicken broth.
Mix well.
Combine milk and egg and stir into hot rice.
Spoon mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add taco mix and refrigerate.
Cut up all vegetables into bite sizes.
Put on serving platter. Sprinkle beef mix on top. Add corn chips and cheese on top. Serve with salad dressing.

title: key lime pie
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 15 minutes.
Add carton of Cool Whip.
Mix until blended.
Put filling into either a graham cracker pie shell or into a butter crust shell.
Chill in the refrigerator for at least 8 hours.

title: arabic bread
directions: Brush pita bread with olive oil; sprinkle with spices.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cut with scissors into fourths. Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: dill dip
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Great dip for vegetables, crackers, etc.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl; add eggs, buttermilk and oil, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: cream cheese vegeburger loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: one big pot of wonderful bean soup
directions: Measure 2 cups beans.
Wash beans.
Place in a large kettle and cover with 2-inches of water.
Add 2 tablespoons of salt and soak overnight.

title: frosted jello
directions: Combine flour, sugar, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick, then add butter.
Cool, then add whipped cream (whipped and unsweetened).
Spread over jello and garnish with nuts or shredded cheese.

title: fruit-filled chocolate dreams
directions: Place foil on cookie sheet.
In small mixer, blend milk, topping mix, vanilla and cocoa; whip at high speed until topping peaks, about 2 minutes.
Continue beating 2 minutes longer until topping is light and fluffy.
Spoon mixture into 5 mounds onto prepared cookie sheet with spoon.
Shape 4-inch shells.
Freeze. Fill center of each shell with fruit.

title: rice and ham salad
directions: Cook rice; toss with French dressing and chill for several hours.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, salt, mustard and pepper.
Add to chilled rice and toss.
Add chopped ham, cauliflower, peas, celery and radishes.
Toss again.
Put in a scooped melon shell, if you want.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: In a skillet, saute Onion in Oil until tender.
Place Biscuit Mix in a bowl.
Combine Eggs and Milk; stir into Biscuit Mix just until combined.
Stir in the Onion, 1 cup of Cheese and 4 teaspoons of Parsley.
Spread the batter into two greased 8 inch round baking pans.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheese and Parsley.
Drizzle with Butter.
Bake at 400 for 15 - 20 minutes or until Cheese is melted and top of bread is lightly browned.
Yield:
12 - 16 servings.

title: oilicious spoon bread
directions: Stir up with sweet milk until thin.
Bake until brown.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to
375°.	Butter	a
2 quart casserole or baking dish.
Cook
the macaroni in boiling salted water until tender, 8 to 10
minutes.
Drain
well
and toss with 3 tablespoons of the butter.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Continue beating until very light.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir.
Add water and vanilla.
Spread into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out onto cloth towel.
Spread on desired amount of jelly.
Roll up.
Wrap with cloth until cool. Slice with serrated or electric knife.
Yields 24 servings. Preparation time is 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add flavoring and milk; mix well.
Add coconut.
Mix and bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no fuss carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Bake in two round 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
I just dump everything in, in order, except for eggs and nuts, then stir in eggs, then nuts.
The carrots will fall apart when you mix, so no need for chopping.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done (approximately 25 to 35 minutes).

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix both puddings and milk according to pudding directions. Mix cream cheese and condensed milk thoroughly and add to pudding mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers, pudding and bananas. Makes a lot.

title: potato magic
directions: You will need an 8 x 10 flat casserole pan.

title: rolled pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the pecans, vanilla, flour, water and salt; mix well.
Roll with palms of hands into finger lengths. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm or shake in bag.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, margarine, milk, dash of salt and marshmallows in a large deep pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boiling. Cook and stir 5 minutes (or until forms soft ball in cold water).
Remove from heat. Add the chocolate bits and stir until completely melted.
Add the vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Pour in buttered dish. Cool and cut into squares.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all ingredients.
Cook spaghetti.
Add 2 tablespoons oleo and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Mix.
Line greased 10-inch pie tin with spaghetti.
Add hamburger mixture to center. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add Mozzarella cheese to top.
Bake 5 more minutes (or until cheese melts).

title: taco dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and avocado dip or sour cream with mixer.
Spread on serving platter; layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to boiling; boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Combine oleo, shortening and boiling water.
Let cool.
Mix eggs, cold water and sugar in a large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with shortening mixture and add flour.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover; let stand overnight.

title: mushroom fritters
directions: In mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, mushrooms, onion, pimento, salt and celery salt.
Mix together egg yolk and sour cream, stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Beat egg white to stiff peaks.
Gently fold beaten egg white into mushroom mixture.
Heat oil and drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
This only makes 12 fritters each.

title: marinated salad
directions: Heat and pour over ingredients and marinate overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger with onion; drain if fatty.
Add remaining ingredients (except Mozzarella cheese) and mix; simmer a bit.
Pour over spaghetti and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: bread machine rolls
directions: Place ingredients in bread machine in order given. Select white bread cycle. Push start. When cycle is done, remove dough and make into rolls. Place in pan and let rise for 2 hours in a warm place, like oven with light on. After rolls rise, remove from oven. Set oven for 400°. Bake 20 minutes. Turn oven to 350°. Bake another 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, sugar, eggs and oil in a large bowl and mix well.
Stir in pineapple and pour batter into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows and then butterscotch morsels evenly over batter. Carefully push down slightly into batter but not all the way down. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Shake pan once or twice during baking to maintain distribution of marshmallows.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.
Glaze will form on bottom of pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add flour and soda.
Mix well. Add bananas one at a time.
Fold in pecans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter or margarine. In separate bowl, blend pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold together in blender.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Finely grind Oreo cookies. Alternate layers of pudding mixture and cookies, adding gummy worms.
Final layer should be cookies.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg in medium bowl.
Stir in milk and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, just until flour is moistened. Batter will be lumpy.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer on stove for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a medium casserole dish, put butter in the bottom (just spread it with a paper towel or spatula.)
Slice zucchini, do not peel, in thin slices.
Slice the green pepper, onion and tomato. Put the 1/4 cup rice in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Layer the vegetables, sprinkle the top with sweet basil and brown sugar. Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin and carrot salad
directions: Mix ingredients with the amount of mayonnaise to give it the consistency you like.
Mix it together about 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix next 4 ingredients; heat.
Beat the cheeses together.
Stir in the next 4 ingredients.
Place half of the noodles in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan; spread with half of the cheese mixture, half of the chicken and half of the soup; repeat layers.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in a moderate oven about 30 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand 10 minutes. Cut in squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Put stuffing mix on bottom of dish.
Mix asparagus, peas and soup in boiler.
Heat until soup melts.
Pour over crust.
Top with grated cheese.
The amount of cheese can be to your taste.
Bake at 450° until bubbly hot and cheese is melted.

title: microwave onion-beef soup
directions: Slice onions thin.
Combine onions and butter in 3-quart microproof casserole.
Cover.
Cook on High 10 to 12 minutes, or until onions are transparent, stirring once during cooking time. Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook 10 to 11 minutes (or until hot) on High.
Serve in bowls with cheese sprinkled on top.
Makes 6 servings.
Total cooking time: 20 to 23 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix together butter, lemon juice, poppy seed, Beau Monde seasoning and onion.
Cut bread into slices 3/4 way through loaf. Spread on butter, mix and add Swiss cheese into cuts.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: applesauce cake plus
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins, nuts, crushed pineapple and cherries.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: cashew salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, cheese and cashews in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend the remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over the lettuce, cheese and cashews.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Use tube pan.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, alternating with flour and baking powder.
Add coconut, pecans and flavorings.
Fold in orange juice.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Use icing of your choice or dribble.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Shred cheeses on bottom of pan.
Layer chilies, then cheese again.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat yolks, milk, flour and salt until smooth.
Fold in egg whites into yolk mixture and spread over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in cake pan.

title: black walnut drops
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; blend in along with sour cream.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonful on buttered cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be iced with chocolate butter cream icing.
Yield: 6 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in large airtight container.
Use within 6 months.
Makes 17 cups.
To mix:
Add 3 Tbsp. of mix with 1 c. boiling water or 1 1/2 c. mix to 2 quarts hot water.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Stir milk and soup until smooth.
Arrange in layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in covered, buttered casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine on stovetop the clam juice and soup.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Add clams and half and half (not the whole pint). Salt and pepper.

title: spam casserole
directions: In a large skillet, mix corn, spam and margarine.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Sprinkle 2 Tbsp. flour over mixture while simmering.
Add milk.
Stir until thick.
Add pimento and mix. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: crabbies
directions: Cut 6 English muffins in half.
Combine rest of ingredients; spread on muffins.
Cut into fourths (quarters); freeze until ready to use.
Place in broiler for 5 to 7 minutes, until bubbly.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain fat.
Add onion and cook until tender. Remove from heat and add soup.

title: karen's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water. Boil for 30 to 40 minutes, then remove from water and break into pieces. Mix sour cream and cream of chicken with chicken breasts and put in casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Break up crackers and put on top. Bake another 5 minutes.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Empty the lemonade and limeade into a large container, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir and freeze.
When ready to serve, scoop into glass and add Sprite to make slushy.

title: company hamburg casserole
directions: Cook noodles; set aside. Cook hamburg and set aside.
In saucepan, combine soup and all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add to hamburg and noodles.
Put all in greased casserole.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Chop onion fine.
Saute in butter until browned.
Drain can of corn, then mix corn, uncooked noodles, milk, soup and hot dogs together.
Take mixture and add toast and thin slices of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup of sugar, and set a side.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients:
sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter, pour peaches and sugar over that--do not mix, just pour over.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees, or until golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots; drain and cool.
Heat soup, vinegar, oil, sugar and dry mustard until sugar melts.
Mix all together well and refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix dry ingredients in plastic container (like one from ice cream) and shake.
Add oil, vinegar, mushrooms and other ingredients.
Leave out at room temperature five hours, stirring occasionally, then refrigerate.
Make the night before and usually double the recipe as they go quickly.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients (sauce is separated) thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon if you like the flavor. Pour 8 ounce can of tomato sauce over all.
Bake one hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; add alternately with chocolate syrup to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips. Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Prepare noodles according to package. Over low to medium heat, in saucepan, melt butter. Add cream and cheese. Heat until cheese melts. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add chives or parsley for color. Stir sauce into cooked noodles and serve.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom and sides of an 11 x 7 inch baking dish.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix ground beef, applesauce, rice, onion, salt and pepper. Shape into 2-inch meatballs.
Place l layer deep in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour tomato sauce over meatballs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 14 to 16 meatballs.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes; do not peel.
Cut in wedges (6 or 8 per potato).
Rub wedges with mayonnaise, using a pastry brush or your hand.
Lay the wedges on a baking dish, sprayed with Pam or covered with foil.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt on both sides. Bake in moderate oven until tender.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cut dates in small pieces and put in mixing bowl; put soda in cup of hot water and pour over dates and cool.
Add sugar, butter, egg,
walnuts, vanilla and flour and mix real well.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at a temperature of 350°.

title: squash and onion casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions until tender.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup and eggs.
Top with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: hot pineapple eggnog
directions: Combine egg yolks, 8 egg whites and 1 cup sugar; beat thoroughly.
Bring pineapple juice to boiling point.
Add cream and reheat.
Pour over first mixture, stirring constantly.
Beat remaining egg whites and add sugar.
Fold egg whites into hot mixture.
Sprinkle with orange rind.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail well.
Mix all together.

title: chunky chicken noodle soup(low sodium recipe)
directions: Combine chicken, 4 cups water, celery leaves, poultry seasoning and thyme in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Strain broth; discard celery leaves and fat.
Return broth to a Dutch oven; add green onions and remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Bone and coarsely chop chicken. Add to broth mixture and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: daisy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix in top of double boiler or heavy pan to where it won't stick.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 12 sandwiches.
Serve on buns.

title: pork chops and cabbage
directions: Brown pork chops in fat on both sides and remove from skillet. Add onion soup, milk, salt and pepper to skillet and blend well. Place alternate layers of potatoes and cabbage in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle each layer with flour. Pour soup mixture over top.
Place pork chops over soup mixture and cover casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well and pour into ice cream freezer.
Tastes much like a "Wendy's Frosty".

title: cheese pastry tarts
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter into flour until very fine.
Roll into a ball and chill for two hours.
Roll dough out on floured board.
Cut into 3-inch circles.
Put 1/2 teaspoon filling of your choice in the middle of each circle.
Dip fingertip in water and wet edge of circle.
Fold circle in half and seal edge with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk. Add oranges and cookies. Stir in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: black forest pie
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies and place in a pie plate like crust.
Fix pudding according to directions on box.
Place pudding on top of crust, then add the cherry pie filling.
Top with the Cool Whip. If you have extra cookies, you can put them on top.

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place cracker crumbs on top. Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars. Add egg, peanut butter and vanilla. Sift flour and baking soda together. Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: glazed club crackers(butterscotch)
directions: Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Melt sugar, butter and oleo.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Spoon liquid over crackers and bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove crackers to wax paper to cool.
Store in covered container.

title: quick lo-cal punch
directions: Mix together and pour over ice.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: speedy rolls
directions: Step 1:
Place lukewarm water, sugar and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Add salt and 2 c. sifted flour.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.

title: basic cornbread(corn sticks, corn muffins and corn squares)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, milk and shortening in a separate bowl.
Add to dry ingredients; beat lightly until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased muffin, cornstick or square pan.
Bake in preheated oven (450°) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Roll level tablespoonfuls of the mixture into balls the size of walnuts (makes about 60) and arrange them on a jelly roll pan close but not touching.
Freeze until hard, then pack in a gallon size freezer food storage bag.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add celery and onions to taste.
Rinse macaroni when cooked.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and sour milk (with soda stirred into milk).
Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Add pinch of salt. Place in greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: carrot medley
directions: Wash carrots.
Peel.
Cut into 1-inch chunks.
Cook until done. Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low heat until pepper and onions are done.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice or eat with vegetables.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Boil butter and honey until foamy; goal is to have a firm coating for popcorn.
Pour over popped popcorn and salt to taste. (If syrup is too soft, cook longer or decrease honey.)

title: cherry chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven

Grease

mix with pudding mix.
Add eggs, water and oil. Blend
