at low speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Batter
will
be thick.
Turn into prepared pan; spread evenly. Bake 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Turn out completely.
Top with Glaze.

title: polly's fruit soup
directions: In saucepan, heat orange juice and tapioca; bring to a boil. Mix sugar, fruit cocktail, peaches, pears, bananas, apples and strawberries together in a large bowl.
Add all juices from canned fruit.
Serve cold.

title: el rancho chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Pour over chicken and bake at 425° about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top the last 10 minutes, until melted.

title: yummy coconut cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 cake pan bake cake according to package directions. After it cools 5 minutes, poke holes throughout cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with Creme of Coconut and pour over cake while warm and then cool completely.
(You may not need quite all of this mixture.)

title: fast-fixing chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour oil in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Tilt pan to cover bottom.
Put cake mix, pudding, eggs and water directly into pan. Stir with a fork until well blended.
Pour chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Set aside.
In a skillet, cook sausage, green pepper and onion over med. heat for 5 minutes.
Add to bean mixture.
Bring to a boil over med-high heat.
Reduce to low and cook for 20 minutes.
In a small bowl combine cornstarch and water until smooth.
Slowly pour into bean mixture, cooking and stirring until it thickens approximately 1-2 minutes.	Place rice in bowls and top with beans.

title: banana-jam muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with paper liners.
Beat 1/2 cup shortening and sugar well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Combine 1 2/3 cups flour, oat bran, baking powder and salt. Combine banana and lemon juice.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix toasted bread into tomato pulp.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into buttered baking dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Mix well in order and bake in greased bread pan in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove bread from pan and, while still hot, pour 1/2 cup sugar mixed with juice of 1 lemon over bread.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: grilled steak
directions: Marinate steaks in garlic, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Let set 4 hours before grilling.
The timing will depend on your taste.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put juice, sugar and butter in pan; melt and stir.
Put bread in bottom of baking dish; put crushed pineapple on bread.
Pour hot liquid over mixture and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Fold into pasta.
Add Miracle Whip salad dressing to keep moist.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream; spread in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread refried beans on top of mixture.
Spread salsa on top of refried beans.
Layer chopped tomatoes and cheese on salsa.
Garnish with green onions.
Refrigerate.

title: honey bourbon grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Trim fat from pork. Combine onion and the next 7 ingredients in a large zip-top bag. Add pork and marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Remove pork from bag. Save marinade. Sprinkle salt and pepper over pork. Place pork on grill rack coated with cooking spray. Cover and cook for 30 minutes, turning and basting with 1/2 cup of the marinade.

title: sour cream drops
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg.
Add sifted, dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Stir in dates stuffed with walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool; spread with golden icing.

title: four inch frosting
directions: Mix together sour cream, powdered sugar and coconut.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Frost your favorite 9 x 13-inch cake and refrigerate.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Press one-half of mixture into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Combine next 3 ingredients and cook until clear.
Add vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb and sprinkle top with remaining first mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Beat granulated sugar, margarine and eggs until light and fluffy. Stir in remaining ingredients except powdered sugar.
Spread in pan.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Cool completely; cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 54 cookies.

title: raspberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill until set.
May be served in parfait glasses without crust.

title: chili eggs
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all the ingredients together, including the melted butter.
Pour into pan.
If baking immediately, bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes or until set.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.
Mix together with mayonnaise.

title: aaron's bundles
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar with shortening.
Add beaten egg and molasses.
Dissolve baking soda in milk.
Sift flour and 1 cup of sugar.
Sift cinnamon and nutmeg, then add, alternating, milk and flour.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Grease pans or cupcake tins. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Blend well, thoroughly dissolving sugar until the mixture is somewhat syrupy.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a crock-pot, place roast, cream of mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer on high 5 hours, turning occasionally.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook another hour or until vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegetables to platter.

title: south of the border meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except salsa; blend well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs on all sides; drain fat.
Add salsa to skillet.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix and press in pan.
Cut and chill.
Very good frozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and eggs together.
Roll into balls and press out with a fork.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool, then enjoy.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour covered or until liquid is absorbed.
Serve with steaks, roast beef or baked chicken.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Thaw hush puppies and crumble fine.
Saute onions and celery in 1 stick butter and set aside.
Crumble cornbread and toast together.
Add to hush puppies.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine the cukes, onion and salt; let stand 3 hours in cold water.
Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Put into airtight sterilized jars.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: geneva fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; roll in flour.
Brown on both sides. Line a pan (one chicken fits comfortably in) with foil.
After placing chicken in the pan, cover with 1/2 cup of water.
Seal pan with foil on top.
Cook at 300° (depends on oven) for 1 hour or until tender.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Let cool just a little bit.
Add nuts and colored marshmallows.
Stir and coat completely.
On wax paper, sprinkle powdered sugar in a long line. Spoon mixture to form a log.
(This will make about 4 (18-inch) logs.)
Sprinkle more sugar on the top.
Roll and chill.
(Can be frozen.)
Cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
This will look like stained glass.

title: creepy crawler ice ring(halloween)
directions: Arrange gummy worms in bottom of 5-cup ring mold; fill mold with Gatorade.
Freeze until solid, 8 hours or overnight.

title: barbecue(pork or beef)
directions: If making
pork
barbecue, a Boston butt roast is best; bake as usual.
Use
any
good
beef
roast and bake as usual. After baking, shred or chop meat.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots any way you desire. Cook until tender, but not soft; set aside to cool. Drain. Add onion and green pepper.

title: brenda's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: overnight bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening and it will melt as it cools. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cooled milk, shortening and sugar.
Stir well.
Gradually add 12 cups flour, kneading in with hands.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in cold oven to rise overnight, 8 to 14 hours.

title: canned apricot pie
directions: Cook apricots, brown sugar, nutmeg, flour and cinnamon over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with 1/3 tablespoon butter.
Cover with top crust.

title: mom's best coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 pies.

title: winter chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight canister. Mix 3 tablespoons into 1 cup hot water.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Brown veal; put in dish.
Saute garlic and scallions.
Add tomatoes, basil, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper, mushrooms and 1/4 cup wine.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add more wine or tomato juice, if needed.
Pour over veal.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onions.
Combine other ingredients to slow cooker.
Let simmer 1 1/2 hours on low.

title: fresh coconut cake with sour cream frosting
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions, adding coconut flavoring.
After cake bakes, prick layer with fork and spoon coconut milk over layer.
Mix together sour cream, Cool Whip, sugar and coconut.
Frost layer.
Sprinkle coconut over top of cake.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat.
Mix cake mix, melted margarine, milk and pecans just until holds together.

title: spier's chili
directions: In large pot, saute beef with green pepper, onion and garlic until beef is brown.
Add rest of ingredients, except beans, and simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Stir in beans and simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes a lot but freezes well.

title: helen kern's pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt together; add mixture of salad oil and cold milk.
Stir lightly until mixed.
Round up dough and divide in half.
Flatten each half slightly.
Place between 2 sheets of waxed paper and roll out carefully until dough is desired thickness.
Peel off top paper, lift pastry carefully into pie plate.

title: chicken eddy
directions: * Shrimp or crab meat may be used instead of chicken.
Use same amount (2 cups).

title: irish soda bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt, caraway seed and baking soda in large mixing bowl. Stir in dissolved yeast.
Melt butter in small saucepan, then heat buttermilk.
Add to yeast mixture and beat well.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups flour to make a soft dough with mixture leaving sides of bowl.
Stir in raisins.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Arrange meat and vegetables in casserole in alternate layers. Pour in soup and water with salt and pepper.
Cover casserole and bake in 275° oven for 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick grill savory chuck steaks
directions: Prepare grill.
In small bowl, combine steak sauce, brown sugar, lime juice and red pepper; reserve 2 tablespoons marinade; set aside.
Place beef steaks in plastic bag with marinade, turning to coat.
Close bag securely and marinate 10 minutes; do not chill. Pour off marinade and discard.
Place steaks on grid over medium coals.
Grill 14 to 20 minutes for rare to medium, turning once. Brush with 2 tablespoons reserved marinade during last 2 minutes of cooking.
Salt to taste.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Line a greased pie plate with rolls or pizza crust mix to make a crust.
Brown hamburg and onion together.
Drain off fat. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Add enough spaghetti sauce to make the consistency of sloppy joes.

title: bread pudding(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart batter bowl, combine bread cubes and milk; let stand 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour in an 8-inch glass ring mold.
Place on inverted glass pie plate. Microwave on 70% power for 10 to 12 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese; mix well. Add remaining ingredients; mix and pour into large dish to gel.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce together until smooth.
Layer in a shallow 8 or 9-inch dish.
Top with chopped ingredients and cover with shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in square baking dish in oven.
In medium mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and milk.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into hot baking dish.
Add frozen fruit of your choice.
Do not mix in.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with milk and sugar or ice cream.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saut onions and garlic in olive oil until transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until well blended, about 4 to 6 hours.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Heat cream in medium saucepan; when it begins to simmer, stir in cheese a little at a time.
Stir continuously over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add butter a little at a time.
When all butter is in and sauce is smooth, remove from heat and beat a small amount of it into the egg yolks; return the egg yolk mixture to the sauce and stir it in thoroughly with a wire whisk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Mix with cooked noodles (al dente) and toss.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: panned zucchini with garlic
directions: Trim zucchini into 1/4-inch rounds.
Place in a colander and sprinkle liberally with salt.
Allow to stand in colander for 20 minutes, then rinse well and drain.
Heat butter and olive oil in skillet.
Saute garlic.
Rinse and drain zucchini again and add to garlic in skillet.
Saute over high heat until tender, turning frequently.
Serve immediately.
Should serve 8.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Top with the toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: perfect pie crusts
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and sugar well.
Add the egg, then the vinegar, then the water last.

title: jeff's pot roast
directions: Mix flour with herbs and spices; rub into meat, coating completely.
Heat 2 tablespoons shortening in a large, deep skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat on each side for 8 minutes. Reduce heat; pour in 1 to 2 cups hot water.
Cover; simmer roast for 1 hour before adding vegetables and a dash of salt.
Cover; simmer/cook vegetables and roast together until they are tender (about 45 minutes to 1 hour).
If desired, take roast from pan along with vegetables.
Make gravy from liquid in pan.

title: gobs
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa; add butter and add sour milk and water.
Add water last.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 450° for about 5 minutes.

title: cheese sandwich
directions: Put 1 slis of bred on plate.
Get cheese and put on bred.
Get the other peese of bred and put it on the peese of cheese.
Put in microwave for 20 sekonds or untill cheese is meltid, then take out and enjoy eating.

title: chris' sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
Make up cinnamon sugar and pecans mixture.
Spoon half the batter into pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on batter.
Spoon remaining batter over cinnamon. I always sprinkle a little cinnamon sugar on top of batter (no pecans).
Pour half into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Keep checking.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
In separate bowl add flour with baking powder and salt.
Add this gradually to first mixture with half and half cream.
Beat until it is mixed well and then add vanilla and lemon.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour. Check to be sure it is done by using a toothpick.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook each item separately; drain okra and butterbeans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season with salt and black pepper. Cook on medium temperature for 1 hour.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in an uncooked pie shell; bake until a knife stuck in center comes out clean.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hillbilly spaghetti
directions: Dice bacon and onions and fry until done (do not drain). Add tomatoes and heat.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: knobby apple cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix.
Pat in apples and mix well. Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Saute onions in oleo.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add peeled, sliced peaches and lemon juice.
Cook until mixture thickens and boils; stir frequently. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole; keep peach mixture hot in oven.

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Steam hamburg, onion, celery, soy sauce and water for 10 minutes.
Add soups and rice.
Cook slowly 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: chili cheese puff
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until fluffy and lemon colored. Add the flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and butter; blend until smooth.
Stir in the chilies.
Pour in buttered, 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bonnie's potato bread rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add potatoes, salt and eggs.
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup of warm water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat in 2 cups flour and remaining water.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Shape into a ball; do not knead.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Put rolls into greased pans.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
45 rolls.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix well with spoon in glass or plastic bowl. Pour into 2 large, well-greased and sugared (mix a little sugar and cinnamon together) coated loaf pans or pound cake pan not over 1/2 full. You sprinkle extra cinnamon and sugar mix on the top of batter. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes. Let cool, then enjoy.

title: beef stew
directions: Season stew meat to taste and flour to the meat.
Put oil, bell pepper, green onion and yellow onion in large pot.
Brown onions about 2 minutes; add stew meat.
Brown the meat about 3 minutes, then fill the pot about half full of water.
Add beef stew seasoning.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all of the ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan. Boil for 1/2 to 3/4 of an hour.
Spoon over grilled chicken.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Heat sugar, milk, shortening, chocolate and salt to rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil, without stirring 1 minute. Place saucepan in bowl of ice and water; beat until frosting is thick.
Stir in vanilla.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Form into small balls in shallow baking pans.

title: super tuna casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, peas, tuna and crushed potato chips.
Garnish with pimientos.
Put casserole into oven at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll biscuits into balls.
Melt margarine.
Roll biscuit balls in margarine.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Roll balls into sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place balls in a Bundt pan.
Drizzle with honey.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Invert onto plate immediately.
Pick and eat.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cover cookie sheet with wax paper; set aside.
Thoroughly cream butter, sugar and milk in small mixing bowl; blend in vanilla and almond extracts.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Mold just enough mixture around each cherry to completely cover cherry. Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Cover loosely; chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: large cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly combine ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: The supreme cobbler, made with lots of juicy peaches and bits of cooked pastry, baked in a flaky lattice crust.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Flour fruit, raisins and nuts (I use a pastry sheet to do this).
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.

Add flavoring. Combine with flour mixture (I also do this on the pastry sheet). Prepare an 8-inch round by 5 or 6-inch deep cake pan by cutting 2 layers of brown paper to fit in the bottom and up the sides of the pan.
Grease each layer with Crisco.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours or until done (when shrinks from side of pan) or begin in cold oven at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Place pan of water on rack below cake.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk; keep beating until mixed good.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust; refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Add cherries on top.

title: double chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Blend for 4 minutes, then let stand for 15 minutes.
Oil and flour Bundt pan. Pour half of the batter into the Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half the chocolate chips onto batter.
Pour on the remaining batter. Sprinkle with remaining chips.
Slightly press chips down into batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix pudding and juice.
Dump together with fruit.

title: joanne's easy dessert
directions: Combine the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes; cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and cut up chicken.
Place the pieces in an oblong Pyrex dish (2-quart).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash, peel and slice zucchini.
Cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and blend in blender or use potato masher. Add onion, eggs, sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Add salt and pepper and blend or mix with hand egg beater.
Pour mixture into shallow baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Combine and let stand the dates, baking soda and boiling water. Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar and beat in the vanilla, eggs, salt and flour.
Add dates to mixture.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil.
Add 22 whole Ritz crackers; boil 2 minutes (do not stir).
Pour into pie shell.
Top with cinnamon, nutmeg and dots of butter.
Cover with top crust and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend the flour, shortening and salt with pastry blender.
Add water, vinegar and egg; mix well.
Roll on floured board.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: wacky cake(very moist)
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing after each.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, Blue cheese and butter.
Stir in olives and chives.
Chill slightly.
Form in ball.
Chill well.
Press walnuts on ball.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes three cups.

title: puffed pancakes
directions: Whisk together at last minute.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix pineapple and milk.
Add orange drinks.
Place in freezer until firm.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients, then stir into molasses mixture.
Chill 3 hours.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with gingerbread cutter. Place 1 inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
While still warm, press in raisins or candy pieces (M&M's, etc.) or cool and decorate with icing.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: affy tapple salad
directions: In a medium sauce pan, stir together flour, sugar, tapioca, vinegar and reserved pineapple juice.

Cook over medium heat until thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and chill.	In a large bowl, combine the pineapple, apples, peanuts and chilled tapioca mixture. Fold in whipped topping and chill for at least one hour before serving.
Makes 12 servings. 281 calories per serving.

title: louisiana shrimp casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions, bell peppers and garlic in butter until crisp and tender.
Add shrimp, cook 3 minutes longer. Stir in soup, rice, parsley, lemon juice, seasonings and crawfish tails.
Add bread soaked in milk.
Mix well.
Spoon into buttered shallow 2 qt. casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then mix together the liquids. Add to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from the side of the pan.
Add any color of food coloring (your choice).
Knead on wax paper.
Put in plastic container to store.
Great for school projects.

title: spicy cashew cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg in large mixing bowl.
Measure dry ingredients and stir into shortening mixture.
Stir in chopped cashews.
Roll dough in 1 inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw dough and spread into rectangle.
Spread a little oil from salad pepper on the dough.
Layer on cheese, salami and peppers. Roll into long loaf.
Press dough at seam and pinch seams to seal. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until loaf is golden brown.
Slice and eat or cool and freeze.
You can use any meat or cheese combination you like. Makes 2 loaves.

title: lemon buttered potatoes
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter and add remaining ingredients except potatoes in serving dish; pour butter mixture on potatoes.

title: sour milk huckleberry muffins
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix together egg, margarine and milk.
Blend into dry ingredients until dry particles are just moistened.
Fold in huckleberries.
Bake in greased muffin pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onion until soft.
Drain and set aside.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots together and add to squash.
Melt margarine and mix with dry stuffing mix.
Press 1/2 of stuffing mixture into greased baking dish.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: italian lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne in boiling salt water (until tender) about 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Separate lasagne and hang over edge of colander to allow for easier handling later.

title: turkey and lentil casserole
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, in a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook turkey until drumsticks are browned on all sides.
Remove to a 5-quart Dutch oven.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool.
Stir in Cool Whip and bitter chocolate.
Put into graham cracker crust.
Freeze and serve!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip coconut bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until smooth.
Beat in flour, salt, soda, vanilla and coconut.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (until pick inserted comes out clean).
Cool completely in pan on rack. Cut in 18 bars.

title: cocoa cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Place egg whites in large bowl.
Beat until frothy; add oil, yogurt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 28 minutes. Do not overcook!
Dust with confectioners sugar and cut into squares (only 3 grams fat!!!).

title: unforgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites until foamy. Add sugar, 2 spoons at a time. Beat until stiff. Add vanilla. Fold in nuts and chips. Drop by teaspoon on a foil-lined cookie sheet. Turn off oven. Place cookies into oven.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: Mix together stuffing mix and butter; press into 9-inch pie plate.
Heat remaining ingredients together; turn into pie shell. Arrange border of stuffing crumbs on top of pie.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: nuts and bolts(appetizer)
directions: Melt butter or oil in large roasting pan.
Add cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Combine the last 4 ingredients and add to roasting pan.
Cook, covered, in a 225° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook until brown and crisp, stirring often.
Cool; put in quart jars and keep closed until needed.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, oil, egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Let chill in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Roll into small balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with bottom of glass, dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully and do not overcook.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut dough into 1/4-inch slices; place into a round pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Using floured fingers, press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 11 minutes, or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Let cool.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Spread over cooled cookie crust.
Arrange the fruit and enjoy!

title: chewy cheese cake
directions: Mix together ingredients, except chocolate morsels, and spread on top of dough mixture.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Mix and sift together first 5 ingredients.
Blend in bowl the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gold rush punch
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour in club soda and garnish with mint and cherries. Makes 10 servings.

title: quick lemon broccoli rice
directions: In saucepan over high heat, heat broth to boiling.
Add broccoli and carrot.
When starting to boil, reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice, lemon juice and pepper.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff rice with fork before serving.

title: incredibles(like reese peanut butter cups)
directions: Combine butter and crumbs.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with melted chocolate.
Chill. Cut into squares.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice and steam yellow summer squash.
Make sauce in large bowl.
Mix well.
Add squash and mix.
Place in casserole/baking dish.
Top with crumbs; dabs of butter (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruited almond custard
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix 1/4 cup of the sugar, the salt and the cornstarch.
Stir in milk.
Put over medium heat and cook, stirring until slightly thickened.
Beat egg yolks until thick, then stir in small amount of hot mixture.
Stir back into saucepan and cook, stirring, until sauce bubbles up.
Remove from heat.
Pour into bowl.
Stir in flavorings.
Cool.
Distribute fruits evenly in shallow 1 1/2-quart lightly buttered baking dish.
Cover with cooled custard.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff, then gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff.
Spoon lightly on pudding.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: callaway gardens muscadine bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating
in one at a time.
Mix in dry ingredients and milk. Stir in muscadine sauce and chopped pecans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for approximately 50 to 60 minutes.
Use a greased and floured loaf pan or muffin tins lined with cupcake papers.
Baking time may be less for muffins.
Insert toothpick in center of bread; when it comes out clean, bread is done.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Deep fry Pi Mei Fun in hot oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and chill.
Combine all dressing ingredients, beating in blender.
Just before serving, add Pi Mei Fun and dressing.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients together. Serve over lettuce leaves and garnish with tomato wedges.

title: arizona skillet dinner
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil.
Add the next 6 ingredients; saute for 4 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Toss with cooked and drained macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese grits
directions: Slowly pour the grits into the boiling salted water, stirring constantly until mixed.
Cook 2 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When grits are cooked, add butter, cheese and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: it is really better than sex? cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare yellow cake mix as directed using a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan and bake for 10 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crackers on top and put margarine over. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs until light.
Add oil, followed by dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients that have been rolled in small amount of flour.
Bake in prepared tube pan at 300° or 325° until firm (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: oven fried turkey cutlets
directions: Combine egg and oil in a shallow dish.
Beat well and set aside.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in a shallow dish. Dip turkey in egg mixture.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: In a large skillet, saut the chicken, green pepper and onion in oil until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are crisp-tender. Add the corn, broth, salsa, salt, chili powder if desired and pepper; bring to a boil. Stir in the rice; cover and remove from the heat. Let stand for 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Yield: 6 servings.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables to bite size.
Heat the wok (use high heat). Add the oil.
Add vegetables all at the same time.
Stir and turn the vegetables so that oil will coat each piece of the vegetables. Keep stirring constantly; add salt to taste.
Add the water and cover the wok immediately to let the vegetables cook for about 5 minutes, until most of the water has evaporated.
You need to be very careful not to let all the water evaporate.
You may have to add a little more water to finish cooking.

title: lye soap
directions: Heat fat and strain through a cloth.
Measure 2 quarts and set to cool.
Mix 1 can lye into 1 quart water and stir until lye dissolves.
Do not use aluminum utensils and be careful not to splash on yourself.
Stir.
Let cool for about 1 hour.
Pour lye slowly over fat, stirring slowly until lye and fat are thoroughly blended.
Add 1/2 cup household ammonia.
Add 2 tablespoons Borax dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Stir until mixture is the consistency of honey.

title: sherbet party punch
directions: Place half of the orange sherbet into a large punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place scoops of remaining sherbet on top of punch.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread dough thaw and raise.
Roll to oblong shape.
Spread on soft oleo and garlic powder or garlic salt.
Cover with sliced pepperoni, leaving 1-inch sides.
Cover meat with slices of Mozzarella and Provolone cheese.
Fold in sides and roll up, starting at one end.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, crease side down.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, 1/2 hour (keep watching). Serve warm.
Can be reheated.
Also freezes good.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix in milk, flour and sugar.
Arrange fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, vanilla and jello.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll in small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out using flattened bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
The color of jello used determines the color of cookies.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add half the milk.
Stir.
Add beaten egg.
Then rest of the milk.
Heat Crisco in iron skillet or pan.
Pour half of the melted Crisco into bread mixture.
Pour mixture in skillet or pan and cook till brown at 400°.

title: cheese strata
directions: Ingredients, other than bacon, should be prepared and mixed together the evening before cooking.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Combine sausage with all other ingredients.
Pour mixture into casserole dish, then chill overnight.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a bread loaf pan, about 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk, soda and bananas and mix to blend.
Fold in flour and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake about 55 minutes.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool before slicing.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil in pan and heat, but do not boil.
Set aside to cool, then add vegetables, including juice. Let set for several hours.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
(This makes the largest Tupperware cake taker full.)
Remove from freezer 5 hours before serving. Chop up with fork and add two 2-liter bottles of ginger ale.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Cook onion in fat until golden brown.
Add meat and seasonings; brown.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole, greased.
Mash potatoes.
Add milk, egg and salt.
Spoon in mounds over meat mixture.
Bake in oven at 350°. Serves 6.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, celery and onions together; drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and water, then mix all together.
Grease casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing in bottom of pan.
Mix vegetable and soup mixture together and pour into pan.
Sprinkle cheese and stuffing on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except raisins and nuts; add these last.
Pour into prepared tube pan or 3 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked meat balls
directions: Mix together ground chuck, cracker crumbs, eggs and onion. Shape into balls.
Cover with mushroom gravy.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour; turn meat balls and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Slice French bread lengthwise.
Mix oleo, olives, Miracle Whip and onions together.
Season with garlic powder.
Spread equal amounts to bread halves.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and mix.
Add pineapple, 1 1/2 cups cold water and bananas.
Pour 1/2 in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set.
Mix cream and sugar and spread over set Jell-O.
Put on nuts.
Gently pour on other half of Jell-O mixture.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Add cumin, salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic salt.
Set aside.
Melt Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: sugarless apple muffins
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine with oats and dry milk in a large mixing bowl.
Mix beaten egg, oil, apple, raisins and apple juice.
Add to dry ingredients and fold lightly, only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: apricot crunch
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and egg until egg and flour are lumpy. Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Fill with apricots.
Melt the 3/4 cup oleo or butter.
Sprinkle flour mixture on top of fruit.
Pour the butter or oleo over mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "home canned" apple pie filling
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick and bubbly, stirring often. Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pack jars with sliced apples. Fill with syrup.
Process 20 minutes in hot water bath.

title: rolled coconut cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients and enough flour to make a stiff dough. Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until done.

title: homemade silly putty
directions: Mixing ratio:
2 parts glue to 1 part starch.
It needs to dry a bit before it is workable.
It may not work well on a humid day. Store in an airtight container.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Follow directions on chicken bouillon package to determine how many cups of water to add per bouillon cube.
Prepare bouillon and water in a large pot.
Coarsely chop the vegetables and put them in the water along with the tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for about an hour.
If adding potatoes, add them in for about the last 20 minutes.

title: bologna candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk together until it forms a soft ball in cold
water.
Add dates;
cook until it leaves side of pan. Take off
fire
and
add
nuts and coconut.
Beat until thick. Wring a cloth
out	of cold water and shape candy on this in a roll.
Roll up and let stand overnight or several hours.

title: "shoo-fly cake"
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and butter.
Work into fine crumbs. Reserve 1 cup of the crumbs for topping.

title: red velvet cream salad jello
directions: Drain pineapple and save syrup.
Dissolve lime Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in 1/2 cup pineapple syrup.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese until softened.
Beat in cool Jell-O just a little at a time.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and set.

title: broccoli italiano
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: peach trifle
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in 1/2 whipped topping.
Sprinkle sugar over peaches.
Toss gently and set aside.
Place 1/2 cake in bottom of 16 ounce trifle bowl; drizzle 1/2 orange juice over cake.
Top with 1/2 of peaches over cake.
Cover with remaining half of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining whipped topping on top.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yield:
14 to 16 servings.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat into a crust.
Cover with chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pops
directions: Insert a wooden stick into the cut end of each banana half. Place on a baking sheet.
Freeze 1 hour or until bananas are firm. Meanwhile, in a shallow dish, mix cereal, coconut, peanuts and nutmeg.
Brush frozen bananas with syrup, then roll in cereal mixture to coat.
Wrap each pop individually in plastic wrap; return to freezer.
Freeze 2 hours more or until completely frozen.
Serves 4.

title: apple-pear pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out dough for bottom half of pie and refrigerate.
In large bowl, combine pears, apples, honey, nutmeg, ginger and salt.
Add flour.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate, mounding high in center.
Dot with butter.
Top with remaining pie crust; make several slits near center.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Great served warm with whipped cream.

title: challah
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add rest of ingredients, except for flour.
Mix.
Add 4 cups of flour and mix.
Add more flour to make workable dough.
Knead.
Put in oiled bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled.

title: cookie cake
directions: Mix eggs, vegetable oil and sugar.
Stir.
Add oatmeal, coconut, raisins, apples, apple juice and walnut kernels.
Stir. Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Sift together three times before adding to other ingredients.
This provides less fat and sugar and very healthy for children.
Bake at 350° as a cake or use cookie pans.

title: chicken piccata
directions: In shallow bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper. Dip chicken into the flour mixture, coating well. In 12-inch skillet, melt 1 tablespoon "I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!" spread over medium heat and cook 1/2 of the chicken, turning once, until no longer pink. Remove to serving platter and keep warm. Repeat with 1 tablespoon of the "I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!" spread and chicken.

title: waldorf salad with cream cheese dressing
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, orange juice, orange rind and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: pork chops italiano
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Place pork chops in pan.
Cover with potatoes and onions.
Pour tomatoes over chops.
Cover with foil. Cook at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except muffin mix, together.
Add muffin mix and blend well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 50 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Bake 1 layer cake (white).
Cool.
Crumble the cake.
Melt Marshmallow Creme and add chopped nuts and fruit.
Press together in pan.
Garnish the top with cherry halves.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix with mixer.
Then add nuts.
Spread on brown bread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs, one at a time. Stir in carrots
and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes
in a 350° oven.
Frost with cream cheese frosting after cooling.

title: pralines
directions: Put sugar, water and salt in saucepan.
As soon as it starts to boil, add pecans and cook about six minutes.
Add flavoring and butter.
Beat until it begins to lose the shiny appearance and immediately drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
This is really very easy, but takes a time or two to know when to start dropping. Have waxed paper ready before beginning to make candy.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place all ingredients except noodles in the crock-pot.
Cook on High for 4 to 6 hours until the meat falls apart.
Serve over noodles.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Place in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: frosted orange jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and mix.
In the meantime, drain the fruit; reserve 1 cup liquid (to be used in frosting).
Fold fruit into jello that has been chilled. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna and cottage cheese casserole
directions: Mix tuna, oil
from can, cheese, seasonings and 1/4 cup bread crumbs into
beaten
eggs.
Turn
into
oiled
quart casserole and top
with remaining bread crumbs, buttered.
Set casserole in pan of hot
water
and bake in 375° oven about 35 minutes or until mixture is set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook squash and onion in a small amount of salted boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture atop.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables; cook, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: barbecue beans
directions: In skillet, brown bacon and onions.
Add tomato soup and sugar; let simmer 15 minutes.
Pour beans in 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour soup mixture over beans.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: moist banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in pumpkin and water and blend.
Sift dry ingredients together and carefully fold them into the liquid ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Add nuts.

title: lobster soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy pot.
Add paprika, nutmeg and lobster. Cut into pieces.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Heat milk and cream.
Do not boil.
Add to lobster.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add sherry to taste just before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: peachy coffee cake
directions: Coat a 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer, blend egg, 2/3 cup sugar, milk, applesauce and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Beat at low speed 1/2 minute and at medium speed 1 minute.
Fold in peaches and pour batter into prepared pan.

title: creamy baked cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: lemon cake
directions: Crumble
crackers
and
mix
with melted butter.
Press into bottom
of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip the egg whites.
Gradually pour in sugar, making a meringue.
Pour on top of cracker mixture. Bake
in
350° oven about 20 minutes or until golden brown. Meringue
will
fall.
Cool.
Put
lemon
pie filling, then whipped topping on baked meringue.
Refrigerate.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream cheese and milk.
Add pineapple, vanilla, nuts and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shells.

title: pecan puffs(outstanding cookies)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Stir flour and pecans into butter mixture. Roll dough into small balls. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Roll while hot in confectioners sugar. Cool. Roll again in confectioners sugar. Yields about 3 dozen puffs.

title: 5-cup fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip until fluffy; add fruit.
Let sit overnight.

title: zippy franks
directions: Cut wieners into 1-inch pieces.
Put all ingredients into slow cooker and cook on low for several hours.

title: pasta, crab, pod salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to the directions on the box.
(A clove of garlic can be added for flavor.)
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Cook the pea pods in boiling water for about 2 minutes with the red peppers and onions.
Drain.
Add to the pasta.
In a large bowl, combine the pasta, pea pods and crab meat.
In a medium size bowl, combine the mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard and vinegar.
Pour this mixture over the pasta and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Serve over lettuce leaves.

title: disappearing christmas cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil; stir until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes in three 9 inch pans or 9 inch tube pan for 80 minutes at 350 degrees.
Frost with vanilla frosting or serve warm or cold with Cool Whip.
(I use sugar substitute in place of sugar.)

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine
sugar, oleo, cornstarch, cocoa, salt and milk. Cook in	double	boiler	until it begins to thicken, stirring frequently.
Then add slightly beaten egg yolks and cook until thick
(or starts to boil).
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour
into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons
of
sugar and spread this meringue over top of pie and brown in 325° oven.
For larger pie (10-inch), double this recipe.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Grind ingredients in food processor.
Form into patties and fry.
Also can be shaped into balls and fried as meatballs, then served with gravy.
A great way to use up leftover turkey!

title: molasses cake
directions: Put soda in buttermilk.
Beat sugar, eggs and molasses.
Add to dry ingredients.
Pour in a well oiled pan.
Bake at 350°, then cut to desired sizes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Combine celery, soup, pimentos and water chestnuts in casserole. Top with crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peachy apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, peaches, raisins and red hots.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and hot.
Serves 6.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in a little butter.
Dissolve beef cubes in water.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and blend with flour.
Add cream, salt, pepper and beef broth.
Add mushrooms.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumb mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
May be made ahead of time, but place in refrigerator and do not add the cheese and bread crumbs until ready to bake.

title: white christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time; beat well.
Add raisins, cherries, pineapple and nut meats.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add 1 cup milk and 1 cup orange juice alternately.
Lastly fold in egg whites beaten stiff.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in slow oven at 275° to 300° about 2 1/2 hours.

title: pasta & ceci
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings; cook 10 minutes.
Add ceci and cook another 5 minutes.
Cook pasta, drain and add to ceci.
Add grated Romano cheese to taste.

title: egg, ham and cheese breakfast dish
directions: Layer bread, cheese and ham in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat eggs, milk and salt together.
Pour liquid over the top. Let set in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop stems and add to sausage and stuffing mix.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake until mushrooms are tender, about 15 minutes, at 350°.

title: newburg sauce
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add hot milk, return to heat and cook, stirring until sauce is thick.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon paprika, dash cayenne, 2 egg yolks (lightly beaten with 1/4 cup cream and 2 tablespoons sherry).

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put apples, nuts and sugar together.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours, stirring several times.
Combine dry ingredients, then add apple mixture.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Do not use mixer.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans (either 2 loaf pans or a small Bundt pan and a loaf pan).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until toothpick comes out clean).

title: rice krispies butter cookies
directions: Cream and mix well margarine and sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and soda, then add to first mixture.
Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: chips and dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; place into a crock-pot.
Pour in the salsa dip.
Dice both bars of cheese and put into the crock-pot also.
When all the cheese has melted, pour over chips or serve out of the crock-pot.

title: overnight lasagne
directions: Brown the ground chuck.
Drain the grease off the meat and rinse with hot water.
Add Prego to the ground chuck in pan.

In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1/4 of the meat sauce mixture in bottom of pan, then a layer of uncooked lasagne noodles, then 1/4 of the meat sauce mixture, 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese, mixed with cottage cheese.
Repeat noodles, meat sauce and cheese until you have 3 layers.
Pour 1 cup water over outside edge.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Cook hamburger until browned.
Combine all ingredients except soy sauce and simmer in stockpot for 1 to 2 hours.
Add soy sauce to taste.
(I use this instead of bouillon cubes, as it is less salty.)

title: ham and swiss rolls
directions: Split whole pack of rolls with sharp knife.
Mix all of the ingredients and spread on tops and bottoms of rolls.
Layer shaved ham and plenty of Swiss cheese.
Put back in aluminum pans and cut the rolls into squares.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In a medium, non-stick, saucepan prepare pudding mix according to package directions, substituting 1 1/2 c. reserved fruit juices for milk.
Remove from heat and cool pudding completely.
Fold into whipped topping.
Add all fruit and marshmallows to pudding mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: buttermilk cutout cookies
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda together.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out.
Cut out in favorite shapes.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: butterscotch date cookies
directions: Mix together.
Put in loaf pan.
Chill, slice and bake.
